title: mocha cappuccino
directions: Combine coffee and cocoa, stirring until cocoa is dissolved; pour into 2 cappuccino or coffee cups.
Add 1/4 cup skim milk to each cup and stir.
Top each with 1 tablespoon Cool Whip and sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Makes 2 servings.

title: kathy gati's cheese cake
directions: Combine ingredients and press into bottom of 9-inch spring form cake pan to form crust.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in medium bowl.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in melted butter. Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 11 x 13-inch pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool.
Makes 20 large brownies, 25 small brownies.

title: water valley apple pie
directions: Cut apples; sprinkle with some of the sugar, a dash of cinnamon and nutmeg. Cut bread up and put on top of apples. Mix egg, sugar, butter and flour. Pour over bread, making sure to cover each piece.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. You may have to cover top so not to overbrown. Enjoy.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt. Cut in shortening.
Beat milk and egg together and add to mixture. Knead.
Roll out dough and cut biscuits.
Freeze.
Do not thaw before baking.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces (takes about 2 months).
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over open fire about 4 weeks at 465°.
Serves 2,000 to 4,000 people.
If more guests are expected, 2 rabbits may be added; however, most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese, mixing well.
Combine biscuit mix and milk; blend thoroughly.
Add to sausage mixture and mix well. Chill 30 minutes.
Shape into balls and place on broiler pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 36 servings.

title: kreplach
directions: Put four eggs and water in big bowl.
Beat and then add flour enough for soft consistency.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch squares. For filling, saute onions and celery until soft.
Add cooked, diced chicken, salt and pepper.
Fill dough.
Boil in salted water for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve in soup or eat alone as desired.

title: chocolate sundae dessert
directions: Melt peanut butter in microwave.
Add to crackers with sugar. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Follows directions on box for pudding.
Pour pudding over crumbs, putting first chocolate then vanilla and chocolate.
Refrigerate.
Top with chocolate Cool Whip.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Mix fruit and run through coarse blade grinder.
Mix sugar with it; let stand several hours.
Mix jello with 1 cup hot water. When cool, add mixture.
May add nuts.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil apples, raisins and dates in water and cool.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 350° until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and cornstarch and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla and cook until done (thick).
Add coconut.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on pie and brown. Top with coconut.

title: caraway puffs
directions: In bowl, combine yeast, 2 2/3 cups flour and baking soda. Heat together cottage cheese, water, sugar, butter and salt until butter melts.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add eggs, caraway seeds and onion.
Beat on low speed 1/2 minute.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in remaining 2 cups flour.
Place in greased bowl (turning once) to rise.
Let rise, covered, until doubled (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Divide into 24 pieces and place in well-greased muffin pans.
Cover.
Let rise until double, about 40 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine margarine and cream cheese until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill.
Combine brown sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into 24 balls; press into mini muffin pans.
Fill cup 3/4 full with sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a casserole dish and top with another 1/2 package of stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: roast brisket of beef
directions: Combine garlic, salt, paprika, ginger and pepper.
Rub into brisket on all sides, wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven over medium heat; add brisket and cook until browned on all sides (10 minutes). Transfer to plate.
Add onion to pan.
Cover and cook until transparent (2 minutes).
Stir in thyme, bay leaf and chicken broth.
Bring mixture to boil, scraping browned bits around pan. Return brisket to pan.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/4 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots; continue baking 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Transfer to serving plate and arrange vegetables around meat.
Skim fat from juices.
Add 1 tablespoon flour as thickening agent; bring to boil and pour sauce over.

title: lemon angel food bars
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Smooth on cooled bars.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cover chicken with cold water and cook slowly for 3 hours or longer.
Remove chicken from broth and use for chicken salad.
Add seasoning, minced celery and noodles.
Boil 1/2 hour longer. Serve hot.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: toffee bars
directions: Place graham crackers flat in pan.
Combine oleo, butter and sugar and boil 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Add nuts on top. Bake at 350°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch pan; set aside.
Put first 3 ingredients in microwave on High for 10 minutes (stir good).
Then cook in microwave for another 10 minutes on High.
Add Marshmallow Creme, morsels, vanilla and nuts.
Stir good and pour into pan.
Set good before cutting.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in strawberries, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze overnight or a least 6 hours.
Take out 2 hours before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Chill.
Chill pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Pour ingredients into a punch bowl, adding ginger ale just before serving.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan; blend and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips; stir until well blended. Add vanilla and nuts. Spread in lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Cool and cut in squares.

title: wassail
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Cook until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to heat.
Do not boil.
Strain and discard spices.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press into 8-inch or 9-inch pie pan; chill.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cook until lukewarm.
Blend cottage cheese and sweetener until creamy. Slowly add gelatin; mix well.
Pour into crust and chill until firm.
In small saucepan, mix water and cornstarch until smooth. Add pineapple over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Spread over cheesecake and chill 1 hour; makes 12 servings.

title: pecan praline crunch
directions: Mix cereal and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In a 2-cup measuring cup, mix brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir and microwave on High 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes, until boiling. Add vanilla, then baking soda and stir. Mixture will foam. Pour over cereal and mix to coat evenly. Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 20 minutes. Divide between 2 lightly greased cookie sheets to cool. When cool, break into pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: do-nuts
directions: Mix nutmeg, 1 cup flour, ginger, soda, baking powder and salt; gradually add the other 3 1/2 cups flour.
Mix with wet ingredients.
Roll out on floured board (place in refrigerator overnight if you want to).
Roll dough to about 3/8-inch to 1/2-inch thick.
Cook slowly in 2 or 3 pounds of lard.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Line a bowl with plastic wrap and put mixture in bowl.
Leave in refrigerator until well chilled.
Shape into a ball and roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat egg.
Mix with sugar, corn, sour cream and Crisco.
Add corn meal and salt; mix.
Grease heavy cast-iron frying pan.
Coat with dry corn meal.
Pour ingredients into pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Divide mixture evenly into 6 quart size, heavy-duty Zip-top plastic bags.
Freeze.
Remove each bag from freezer as needed.
Let stand at room temperature until mixture is slushy. This is just as good without the Amaretto liqueur.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Make cake according to box instructions.
Let cool.
Punch holes in top of cake and pour condensed milk to cover top.
Cover and refrigerate for at least two hours.
Top with Cool Whip. Crush candy bars and sprinkle on top.

title: mexican corn bread(casserole)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Brown meat, onions and peppers in small amount of oil.
Season with salt and pepper.

Pour half of corn meal batter into 8 to 12-inch Pyrex dish, then layer meat and cheese. Cover with remaining corn meal batter. Bake for 1 hour at 320° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onion and turkey.
Oil pan enough to keep turkey from sticking.
Do not drain any of the following cans:
corn, pinto beans, tomatoes and chili beans.
Add taco seasoning.
Put all together.
Stir well.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Ready to serve. Freezes well.

title: mocha angel cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake as directed on package except stir cocoa into cake mix (dry) and substitute coffee for water.
Bake and cool as directed.
Remove from pan.

title: novy edward's own chili recipe
directions: Cook chuck roast until it can be shredded in small pieces. This can be done atop the stove by putting meat in large pot. Cover meat with water, add onion, cumin and garlic powder.
When meat is tender, remove from heat (save liquid).
Shred and discard fat, gristle and bones.
Return meat to pot of liquid, add tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder, salt and pepper and simmer for a few minutes.
Add can of beans and cook slowly over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Now is the time for the taste test.
Add additional spices to your taste.
When your brow begins to perspire, you have it right!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain juice from cranberries and pineapple.
Add marshmallows and sugar to fruit.
Add whipped cream.
Chill.
Yields 8 servings.

title: gail's beef and tater casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Combine beef, green beans, water, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon around the top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top potatoes with grated cheese and remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: cheese balls
directions: Whip all ingredients together with a beater and chill.
Form into balls and roll in crushed pecans.
Makes 3 average sized balls.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, water and vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and drop into sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: overnight sausage casserole
directions: Put bread in casserole dish; grate cheese over bread.
Fry sausage; drain and put over cheese.
Beat eggs and milk; add mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Dilute soup with 1/4 cup milk; add mushrooms and spread on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: antelope burger
directions: Grind antelope meat and mix with ground beef.
Form into patties, about 6 to a pound.
Make them flat.
Before frying, season to taste.
Serve on split bun with a thin slice of onion, mustard or catsup. Delicious with a vegetable salad.

title: egg nog for a crowd
directions: Place ice cream in punch bowl; chop up and let soften.
Add egg nog and nutmeg.
Can add rum or vodka.
This is very creamy and very tasty.

title: noodles and tomatoes
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cut up cheese and margarine; add and mix into noodles while still hot, until melted.
Cut or mash tomatoes and add to noodles along with the juice.
Mix well and serve.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Butter miniature tins, sides and bottoms.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs and shake out excess crumbs.
Mix well cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and fold in.
Fill pans almost to top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.
(They will fall.)
Mix together sour cream, 2 1/2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Place small amount on inner circle of 48 cooled cakes.
Bake 5 minutes in preheated 400° oven.
You may add a cherry, if you want.
These may be frozen.

title: chocolate crispy cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients, chips and Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
While still hot, punch holes in cake.
Sprinkle 3/4 package Heath Bits on cake.
Mix the Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping; pour over cake.
Cool; cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in cake mix and beat together.
Pour into Bundt cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle a little sugar in pan before adding batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put the 6 quarts of popped popcorn in a large roaster.
Stir in peanuts, if desired.
Boil for 5 minutes: packed brown sugar, oleo, salt, corn syrup and optional maple flavoring.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda to mixture.
This will make it foamy.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Bake at 275° for 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Do not let it get too brown. Dump on waxed or brown paper to cool.

title: quick meal in a dish
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Drain and lay on a baking dish.
Mix potatoes as directed on box.
Pour over pork chops and bake.

title: scalloped potato bake
directions: Spread 4 cups sliced potatoes in bottom of greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, 3/4 teaspoon of salt and dash of pepper.
Pour half of the mixture over the potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed, using the rum extract for a part of the liquid.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch flat pan.
While cake is still warm, punch holes in the cake with a fork and pour mixture of condensed milk and cream of coconut over the cake.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and shredded coconut.

title: spinach & mango salad with shrimp(a quick and easy delight)
directions: Toss everything together and serve with your favorite dressing. Serves 3 to 4.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Mash together and serve with crackers.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, put in a roaster and bake 5 hours at 250°.
Cover and do not raise lid during the 5 hours. More juice can be used if desired.

title: special k bars
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and peanut butter in heavy pan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cereal.
Stir well.
Pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour chips over top.
Set in warm oven until chips melt. Spread chips until smooth.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add sour milk, flour and soda.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crab gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crabmeat, in large bowl.
Cover and let stand refrigerated overnight or several hours.
Before serving, stir in crabmeat.	Adjust seasoning.
Serve with hearty bread.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate almond meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Spray a foil-lined baking sheet with nonstick spray. In a small bowl, mix 2 tablespoons of the sugar with almonds, cocoa and cornstarch. In a bowl, beat egg whites with an electric mixer until frothy. Add cream of tartar and beat on high speed until soft peaks form. Gradually add flavoring and remaining sugar. Beat until stiff and shiny. Gently fold cocoa mixture into meringue.

title: chocolate sundae cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients.
Add egg.
Mix and add next
4 ingredients.
Add raisins and nut meats.
Chill (or freeze to bake later).
Drop spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Bake and freeze for later use.
Cookies will be soft and dark orangish, healthy and yummy.

title: virginia "hillbilly" company sweet potatoes
directions: Blend coconut, nuts, brown sugar and flour.
Add melted butter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: enchilada hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; add soups, sauce and milk.
Heat until mixture is thickened.
Line 9 x 12-inch baking pan with tortillas. Pour in one half of meat mixture.
Add another layer of tortillas.
Pour remaining mixture over the tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: honey chicken(yield:  4 servings)
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Dip chicken in the mixture.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour longer, basting about every 7 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: puffins
directions: Mix the ingredients together.

title: baby back ribs
directions: Place ribs in a large pan.
Cover with water and add pickling spice.
Boil for 1 hour.
Remove ribs and place on outdoor grill. Generously brush on BBQ sauce mixture of brown sugar and Open Pit BBQ sauce.

title: tender noodles
directions: Beat eggs together.
Add cold water, salt and vinegar.
Add 2 cups flour.
Roll out thin; cut into strips and spread on cookie sheets or trays to dry.
Then put in Ziploc bag and freeze.
This recipe makes a lot.
You can freeze them and use whatever amount you want.

title: tarragon-vegetable medley
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish, put the cauliflowerets, carrot strips, onion wedges and water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) about 5 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender, stirring once.
Add green pepper; cover and cook on High for 1 or 2 minutes more or until green pepper is tender. Add olives.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat cookie sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Place crackers in food processor.
Pulse to fine crumbs. Transfer to bowl.

title: eggnog bread
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and eggs; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into butter mixture, alternately with eggnog; mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in pecans, raisins and cherries.
Spoon into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: ornament cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside.
Beat butter or oleo and sugar, eggs and vanilla in bowl until fluffy and light.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll out small portions of chilled dough on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with floured ornament cookie cutters. Place on greased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Transfer to racks to cool and decorate as you wish. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil; heat in oven at 350° until soft.
In saucepan cook onion, garlic, coriander and pepper in butter until onion is tender.
Stir flour in sour cream and add to onion mixture.
Stir in broth and chili pepper all at once.
Add chicken.
Put into tortillas and cover with cheese.

title: b.l.t. chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, barbecue sauce, grated onion, lemon juice and pepper in a small bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill dressing mixture thoroughly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons margarine with onion in a large pan.
Cook on medium heat; add squash and cook for 3 minutes.
Add soup and sour cream.
Stir until blended.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: macaroni and cheese delight
directions: Place Cheddar cheese in microwave for 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Pour over macaroni.
Place diced tomato and salsa over mixture.

title: strawberry divinity fudge
directions: Boil sugar, water and cream of tartar to firm ball stage.
Add strawberries which have been drained as dry as possible.
Let come to a boil again.
Pour slowly, beating constantly, over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat until thick and fluffy.
Pour into well buttered pans.
When firm, cut in squares.
Any thick preserves or candied fruit may be substituted for strawberries.

title: white bean soup
directions: Place beans in a Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boil; boil 2 minutes.
Cover, turn off heat and let stand 1 hour and drain.
Add 6 cups water, bouillon, thyme, salt, onion, garlic and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf; remove 2 cups of bean mixture and place in food processor bowl with metal blade or blender container.
Puree until smooth.
To bean mixture in Dutch oven, add carrot, celery and pureed mixture.
Cover and simmer an additional 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Just before serving, stir in parsley and tomatoes.
Contains 1 gram of fat and no cholesterol.

title: mountaineer apple pie
directions: Combine apples, sugars, cornstarch, spices and salt and let stand while preparing crust. Fit bottom pastry in an 8-inch pie pan. Fill with apple mixture. Drizzle with melted butter. Top with other pie pastry. Seal and flute edges. Brush top crust with milk. Then sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake at 400° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Combine peppers in blender and puree.
Add 1 cup vinegar; blend.
Transfer to large, deep saucepan.
Add remaining vinegar, sugar and cayenne; blend well.
Bring to rolling boil (stir frequently).
Stir in pectin; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, skim, pour into jars and seal.
Makes about 6 half pints.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: grandma reinhardt's homemade noodles
directions: It must be rolled thin, then you put lots of flour on it and fold 4 times, putting flour on each time. Roll very thin each time. Cut very thin strips and lay out to dry. She used to hang them over chairs. When ready to cook, put in strainer and get flour off. Place in boiling water with couple cans of chicken broth. Cook until tender. Drain. Add butter and serve with bread crumbs on top. Use butter in skillet. Add cubes of white bread; keep stirring until brown and crisp. Enjoy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from all fruit except cherries and cook with pudding mix until thick.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 to 5 hours.
Slice bananas and cherries.
Put with other fruit and stir into thickened pudding mixture until well mixed.
Keep refrigerated.

title: barbecue pork on buns
directions: Bring pork to boil in lightly salted water.
Cover; reduce to simmer and cover 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove pork, discard water and cool.
Remove bone and fat; discard.
Coarsely chop lean meat and place in saucepan.
Mix barbecue sauce, catsup and mustard; stir into meat.
Heat thoroughly.
May need to add water to keep meat from sticking.
Makes approximately 18 sandwiches.

title: russian tea
directions: Prepare Base:
Put 6 teabags in hot water. Steep 5 minutes. Add orange juice, pineapple juice and water.
Boil cinnamon sticks in 1 cup of water and add to tea mixture.
Sweeten to taste.

title: stay-abed stew
directions: You need a casserole dish with a tight lid.
Mix all of the ingredients together in casserole dish.
Put the lid on.
Put in a 275° oven.
The stew will cook all by itself and be done in 5 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.
This is great if you don't feel good.
Put everything in and go to bed!
Supper's ready when the family comes home.

title: julie's brownies
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients; mix. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Ice when cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, then banana pulp. Add flour, salt and soda. Stir in pecans and pour into greased and floured tube or loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Better if wrapped while slightly warm.

title: braised pork with broccoli
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a deep skillet; brown the pork all over.
Stir in the garlic, ginger, soy sauce, sherry, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Heat remaining oil in a saucepan and cook the broccoli over high heat for 4 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange on a serving dish and top with the pork.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 c. yellow cake mix. In large bow combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil and mix until crumbly. Grease into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. In same bowl blend softened cream cheese and sugar, add eggs and reserved cake mix. Beat 1 minute at medium speed. At low speed add milk and mix until smooth. Sprinkle chocolate chips over prepared crust in pan, then pour the cream cheese mixture over crust and chocolate chips. Bake at 300° for 45-55 minutes until center is firm. When cool, top with chocolate pudding and chill. Store in refrigerator.

title: pepper steak
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Brown meat in margarine. Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until clear and thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lime punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Add sugar.
Cool.
Add other ingredients, then add enough water to make 1 gallon and 1 pint. Add ginger ale.
Also, sherbet, if desired.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put butter on top and microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth and blend in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered dish and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa, and syrup in a heavy sauce pan. Cook, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Add 2 Tbsp. margarine, stir until well blended.
Bring to a boil;
cover and boil 3 minutes.
Uncover and keep boiling until candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Remove from heat, add remaining margarine, nuts, peanut butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Beat until smooth. Pour into a greased 9 inch square pan.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
Blend in milk and egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Cool before adding walnut meats, vanilla and butter.
Pour into 9-inch baked crust. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Cook at 300° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp stew
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in butter or margarine until soft in kettle.
Stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper; cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, clams and liquid and red pepper seasoning.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture thickens and boils 1 minute. Add okra and shrimp; heat to boiling.
Ladle into a shallow serving bowl; spoon rice around edge.
Or, spoon rice in mounds in center of soup plates; spoon shrimp mixture around rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern style chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender. Add tomatoes, water, beans and chili mix.
Simmer 15 minutes. Top with cheese.
Makes 9 (1 cup) servings.

title: cherry trifle
directions: Mix pudding with milk as directed on package.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Thinly slice cake; brush with orange juice.
Line bottom and sides of a 2-quart glass bowl with cake.
Layer 1/2 pudding, 1/3 cherry filling, 1/2 cup Cool Whip and 1/2 cake slices.
Repeat layers.
Spread remaining Cool Whip all over. Spoon cherry pie filling into center, leaving a 1-inch border. Sprinkle almonds around edge.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: no-fat chocolate pudding cake
directions: Sift together the first 7 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix egg whites, water, corn syrup and vanilla in a medium sized bowl.
Mix in the dry ingredients; stir to blend.
Spread batter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking pan coated with vegetable-oil cooking spray.
Sprinkle the brown sugar over the batter evenly. Pour the boiling water over the batter (water should cover mixture in pan).
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool slightly in pan on wire rack.
Spoon onto dessert plates to serve warm or refrigerate to serve cold.
Makes 12 servings. (Contains 226 calories, 45 g. of fat per serving.)

title: low-fat southern fried chicken
directions: Mix buttermilk and Tabasco sauce.
Mix cornflakes, flour, salt and pepper. Spray cookie sheet with vegetable oil. Dip chicken in buttermilk mixture.
Roll in cornflake mixture. Drizzle oil over chicken. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Blend into egg mixture.
Add nuts and strawberries.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers, vinegar and sugar in a 6-quart kettle.
Stir over high heat until all the sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil hard for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add liquid fruit pectin.
Return to heat; boil hard for 1 minute. Remove from heat; put in jars and seal.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix butter, sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon pink apples
directions: Wash apples and remove cores.
Mix water and brown sugar in baking pan and set apples in.
Fill the center of each apple with red candies.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold; top with cream if you like.

title: swedish meatballs with rice
directions: Blend soup with 1 can water.
Measure out 1/4 cup mixture and combine with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Brown in large skillet in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fry rice in oil until brown.
Add onion and green pepper and brown lightly.
Add other spices and water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pita pizza bites
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Split each bread in half around edge with knife to make 4 rounds.
Place rounds.
Top with onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle with basil and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut each round into 8 pieces.
Makes 32 appetizers, 25 calories per appetizer.

title: steak and potato supper
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Dredge steak in flour. Brown well on both sides.
Place meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour off excess fat.
Scrape browned drippings and add to meat. Arrange potatoes with meat.
Sprinkle onion, parsley, salt and pepper over meat and potatoes.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: grandma sharpe's breakfast cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one 13 x 9-inch baking dish or 2 round pie pans.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Cut shortening into these dry ingredients.
Take 1/2 cup of the crumbs out of the mixed ingredients.
Set these on the side for the crumb topping.
Mix together cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and baking soda. Stir this in with the other ingredients.
Stir in the beaten egg and milk until the batter is smooth.
Use a wooden spoon or electric mixer.
Mix in the molasses, honey and dark corn syrup. Pour batter into the baking dish and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake for 25 to 45 minutes depending on the size of the baking dish used. Bake for breakfast.
Best served warm with cold milk!!!
Good any time of day!

title: baked pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients except milk, dry milk and egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until thoroughly mixed. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and pineapple, juices and all. Add beaten eggs, water and vanilla.
Put in buttered casserole. Dot with oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great with ham dinner.

title: ole-timey tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Roll out on floured board and cut into cookies.
Place lightly greased baking sheet and bake about 5 minutes at 400° or until lightly browned.

title: delma's soup
directions: Rinse chicken and remove any remaining fat.
Place in refrigerator and soak overnight in salted water.
Drain chicken, rinse and put in large pot with water to cover.
While chicken is cooking, cut beef into small pieces.
When chicken is done, remove from pot.
Rinse beef and add to cooking liquid along with bacon. While this is cooking, cut up chicken and add to pot along with bouillon cubes.
Add tomatoes and frozen vegetables.
While cooking, cut up remaining raw vegetables and add with V-8 juice and creamed corn.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add sugar last.
This should be sufficiently salty, but pepper may be added if desired.
Soup may be thinned with water, if desired.

title: "you should taste these" potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes just until peeling turns loose.
(You can boil longer to save baking time in oven.)
Chunk the potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan and salt and pepper to taste.
Combine all other ingredients (except bacon).
Pour over potatoes.
Add crumbled bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender in small amount of water. Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix onion, raisins, salad dressing, sugar and vinegar together; pour over cut up broccoli.
Crumble bacon over salad and serve.

title: twinkie delight
directions: In blender, blend cream cheese plus 1 1/2 cups of milk until smooth.
Pour into bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and puddings.
Mix well.
Split Twinkies in half, longway.
Cover entire pan (9 x 13-inch).
Add pudding layer.
Add whipped topping layer.
Sprinkle nuts.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pecans, potato chips and vanilla. Add flour.
Roll into balls.
Press flat with the bottom of a juice glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake for 14 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and cook with onion until bacon is crisp.
While cooking bacon, mix all other ingredients together, add drained bacon and onions to bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Beat in the eggs.
Add the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in the pineapple, carrots and nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: candy eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in palm of hand to make shape of egg.
Lay on cookie sheet with wax paper on.
Put in refrigerator until they feel stiff.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Melt Velveeta and 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour over drained carrots.
Melt remaining butter; mix with crumbled crackers.
Put on top of carrots.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Heat fruit juice to dissolve jello.
Combine ingredients and chill.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature. Cream the butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk, alternating. Add flavorings. Start in cold oven at 325° on center shelf. Keep oven closed. Test in 1 hour but usually takes between 5 and 10 minutes longer.
Makes a large cake!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl all at once.
Mix well with a fork.
Roll out thin and put in a pie pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix
well the oleo, sugar, vanilla, shortening and egg. Sift and
stir
in
the flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda. Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Roll dough into small balls and flatten with
glass,
moistened
and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° until light tan, about 8 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a large baking dish.
Bake until firm.

title: millionaire candy
directions: You will also need toothpicks for dipping.

title: peanut butter temptations cookies
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and both sugars; beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together and add flour, baking soda and salt. Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place in small muffin tins.
Dough will spread or fill tins.
Bake 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press peanut butter cup in center until only top shows.
Let cool in tins.

title: confetti tuna in celery sticks
directions: Combine the first eight ingredients and spread into celery sticks.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening; add eggs and vanilla. Stir in other ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil in a saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Stir in cornflakes and drop on paper lined cookie sheet. Chill 1 hour. Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: venison chili
directions: Saute the venison in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water; cream shortening and sugar. Add egg, salt, yeast and 2 cups water and mix well.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Set in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Cook rice in broth with bay leaf until done (20 to 25 minutes).
Cool rice and remove bay leaf.
Mix rice with all other ingredients.

title: lemon-basil zucchini
directions: Simmer rice, water, onion and garlic for about 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Cube or grate Swiss cheese into the cooked rice.
Stir until melted evenly.
Add spinach, eggs and milk.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Dump all ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: libby's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in a small bowl. Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl. Stir in pumpkin and spice mixture.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cooked chicken and spaetzle(silver bowl winner 1983)
directions: Brown chicken in pan.
Remove from pan.
Prepare pressure cooker.
Return chicken to cooker, adding onions and seasonings. Add water to chicken.
Close cooker.
Cook at 10 lbs. pressure for 15 minutes.

title: nancy's chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion in a tablespoon of margarine or oil. Mix soups and milk in a large saucepan.
Add celery and onions; stir well.
Add water chestnuts and chicken.
Mix lightly.
In a 7 x 11-inch baking dish, put a layer of dry noodles in the bottom. Add chicken mixture and top with rest of noodles and slivered almonds.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.
A cranberry salad and green peas go well with this.

title: lemon-coconut squares
directions: *Or use lime rind and juice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly and add milk.
Mix sugar and flour separately and then add to egg mixture gradually.
Blend syrup in next and then chocolate paste (fairly thin) and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
(Can use heavy saucepan or iron skillet.)
Pour into baked 8-inch pie crust and add meringue.

title: one crust rhubarb pie
directions: Line the pie shell (uncooked) with diced rhubarb piled high. Mix together sugar, eggs, oleo and flour. Pour over rhubarb and bake very slowly. Beat egg whites and add on top of pie if desired (optional).

title: chicken livers, deluxe
directions: Go through
oysters for crabs, shells, etc.
Slightly salt. Dip in beaten egg.
Roll
in cracker crumbs mixed with corn meal and flour. Let oysters set a
little
to
allow
seasonings
to go in, then fry in Crisco and butter.
Add
more salt to crumbs and add pepper if you like it.

title: cheese ball
directions: Make sure cheese is at room temperature. Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate so you can shape into balls. Use margarine or cooking oil on your hands, form into two balls, roll in chopped nuts. Wrap in wax paper. Refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add consomme and water.
Add wine and sugar.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
When done, cover with croutons.

title: rice dressing(rita's foolproof recipe)
directions: Mix ground meats together with rice.
Add onion tops, bell pepper, celery, onions, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in heavy casserole dish.
Mix soups together and pour over meat mixture.
Cover with tight fitting lid to retain juices and bake 70 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together in large bowl the sugar, flour and salt. Put in saucepan the oleo, cocoa and water. Bring to rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture. Stir well and add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour in greased and floured pan, 9 x 11. Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coconut fruitcake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add fruitcake mix, coconut, raisins and pecans; mix well.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and extract; mix well. Stir in flour mixture alternately with orange juice.
Pack into a greased 10-inch tube pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until cake tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes. Loosen edges with a sharp knife.
Remove from pan to cool completely on a wire rack.
Garnish with candied fruit or pecans, if desired.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of highest quality, pour 1 level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat!
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thugar and beat again.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add elbows, celery, green pepper and onions. Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: spring breeze cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat well.
Blend in yogurt, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread on crust.
Chill.
Top with strawberries.

title: blueberry pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin and evaporated milk until blended.
Cream shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add egg; beat until mixture is fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture, beating well after each addition.
Combine blueberries and flour.
Gently stir into batter.
Fill 18 paper-lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Sprinkle Streusel over top of muffins.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken in nonmetal dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight and turn occasionally.
Use marinade to baste chicken while cooking/grilling.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Salt and flour chicken.
(Put flour in a brown bag; add 2 pieces salted chicken and shake until covered with flour.) Place in a pan, skin side down, cook for 30 minutes.
Turn skin side up and cook another 30 minutes.

title: cutout sugar cookies
directions: Cream together in large mixing bowl the powdered sugar and margarine.
Add egg, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate from 2 hours to several days.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick; cut out with cookie cutters. Decorate with colored sugar before baking or icing after baking. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cookies should not be brown.
Do not overbake.
Remove and cool on cooling rack.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion in skillet with 2 tablespoons oil.
When brown, drain well.
Mix tomato sauce and ground beef mixture with macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese mix (that comes with the macaroni).

title: shrimp bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish. Cover and let cook in oven until piping hot.

title: pizza or taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and mushrooms.
Add taco seasoning. Spread crescent rolls in a pie pan; add meat mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine pie filling, cake mix, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Spread mixture into a lightly greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until done.
Cool.
The creamy chocolate frosting makes these brownies extra good.
Combine sugar, milk and margarine in small saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add milk chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Spread over cooled brownies.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add dry ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla.
Drop by small spoonfuls (about 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon) onto foil lined cookie sheet 3 to 4 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes and peel off foil.

title: italian salad mix
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Bring the rest of the ingredients to a boil and pour over the first ingredients.
Put in a jar and refrigerate.

title: self-rising cherry pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish. Let cool. While cooling, mix flour, sugar and milk in bowl. Pour batter in middle of melted margarine. Do not stir. Pour cherries in middle of batter. Do not stir. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with sour cream.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered in baking dish.
Serve with fresh vegetables of your choice.

title: hot chocolate for ice cream
directions: Boil together oleo, sugar, brown sugar, cocoa and milk for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend together until smooth.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Wonderful for chicken, pork chops, ribs.

title: dressing
directions: Saute with butter the onion and celery.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered, 15 minutes uncovered.

title: fresh mex salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion and pepper in food processor so that some chunks remain.
Finely chop garlic, cilantro and pepper.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and let set for 2 to 3 hours (in refrigerator).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In a large pot, heat 1 cup water and dissolve bouillon cube in it.
Slice zucchini and add to pot.
Cook until tender.
Add crumbled bacon.
Puree in blender with 3 additional cups of water. Combine in pot with canned bouillon; heat through.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Serve with a generous sprinkle of Parmesan cheese on top.

title: lemony fruit dressing
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine sugar and flour.
Stir in lemon peel, juice, egg and marshmallows.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture thickens slightly and marshmallows melt.
Cool. Fold in mayonnaise.
Cover and chill.
Serve with fruit salads or use as a dip for fresh or canned fruits.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, beef and onion.
Drain some juice from all beans. Save in case you need during baking.
Mix all together.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves about 12.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add pineapple. Pour into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle bread on top.
Pour on melted butter.
Bake at 350° until brown and solid, about 1 hour. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Delicious with ham dinner!

title: edible play doh
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It will be very stiff.
Mold like Play-Doh and then eat it.
Kids love to help with this.

title: zucchini-eggplant bake
directions: Saute onion, peppers, eggplant, garlic, salt and pepper in 1/2 olive oil.
Place in baking dish.
Arrange zucchini and sliced tomato on top.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 olive oil, salt and pepper. Bake with cheese and flavored bread crumbs on top in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix in all ingredients. Dip in rye, French or pumpernickel bread.

title: cajun coke chicken
directions: Wash chicken(s) thoroughly.
Rub down with olive oil and sprinkle spices inside cavity and rub thoroughly over bird.
Rub salt heavily on outside of chicken and lightly on inside.
Place chicken head side up on can of Coke and place in shallow pan in oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.	It may also be placed on grill making sure not to cook directly over fire.
Chicken will be ready when legs are loose and skin is golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: string bean casserole
directions: Place beans in a saucepan and cover with water. Cook for 8-10 minutes or until crisp-tender. In a skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter or margarine until tender. Stir in tomatoes, sugar, salt, bay leaf and cloves. Simmer for 10 minutes. Drain beans. Add to tomato mixture. Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until heated through. Discard bay leaf and cloves. Makes 8-10 servings.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Scrape and dice carrots.
Cook until just tender in slightly salted water.
Drain and cool.
Slice onions and peppers.
Layer with carrots in a glass bowl.
Mix soup, vinegar, oil and sugar. Beat well.
Pour over carrots.
Cover bowl and refrigerate.
Let marinate at least 24 hours.

title: muskmelon pie
directions: Cook and mash the melon. Add 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, nutmeg, butter and well beaten egg yolks.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add filling to baked 8-inch pie crust.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Cover filling with meringue and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems for stuffing, keep stems. Chop mushroom stems and onion.
Set aside.
Chop raw bacon and fry until almost done.
Add onions and stems.
Continue to fry until done.
Drain bacon and onion mixture.
Place in food processor (I just mix mine well), add room temperature cream cheese, and mix well.
Put heaping spoonfuls of mixture into mushroom caps.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Bake
cake
according to directions, making two layers, approximately
8-inches
in diameter.
Split both layers horizontally
after cooling.
Blend sugar, sour cream and coconut. Chill. Spread
all	but
1	cup of chilled mixture between the four layers
of cake. Blend the remaining cup with the whipped cream and
spread over top and sides of cake. Seal in airtight container
and
refrigerate
for
days before serving. Keep refrigerated.

title: corn soup
directions: Make roux (medium brown color).
Add onions and bell peppers. Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato products and water; mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer, partially covered, for 1 hour.
Great with cornbread.

title: oven style fried chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk and set aside.
Combine potato flakes and dressing mix.
Dip breast in
egg mixture and roll in potato mixture. Melt butter in a shallow baking pan and arrange chicken breast into.
Bake at 400 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: croutons
directions: *Stack slices and trim off crusts.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: rice
directions: Put rice and water together and cook it.
Eat with butter on it.

title: mushroom crust quiche
directions: In a frying pan over medium heat, melt 3 tablespoons of the butter.
Add
mushrooms
and
cook	until
soft;
stir in crushed crackers.
Turn mixture into a well-greased 9-inch pie pan and press evenly into bottom of pan and up the sides.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind up berries and add sugar.
Grind up orange with peeling, too.
Mix together.
Add grapes and pecans just before serving.

title: cloud topped peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine evaporated milk, sugar, salt and butter.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter morsels. Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Spread into foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
Chill 30 minutes.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Stir until smooth. Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar and walnuts; stir until blended.
Spread over peanut butter fudge. Chill until firm.

title: texas hash
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Simmer onion and green pepper in margarine until yellow.
Add ground beef; stir in cooked tomatoes, uncooked rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, removing lid last 15 minutes.

title: mexican delight
directions: Saute meat, onions and garlic together.
Add tomatoes, beans and olives; simmer 10 minutes.
Cover with tortillas and American cheese.
Cover and simmer until cheese melts, about 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: garry's pork casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt over pork chops and fry in cooking oil.
Set aside to cool.
In a large pan, cook noodles in water.
Add salt and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup and peas. Simmer while you chop pork chops into chunks.
Add pork chops and cook an additional ten minutes on low heat.
Serve.

title: turkey chili
directions: Spray cold pan with canola oil.
Cook turkey and celery.
Use a meat fork to break turkey into pieces.
Cook until no longer pink.
Stir in remaining ingredients, tomatoes, juice, sauce, beans, spices and beef, if desired.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer at least 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Serves 4.
Can be doubled easily.
(Serving has 4 grams of fat and 380 calories.)

title: reese's cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and roll into small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet, not too close together. Press a candy kiss in the center of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes only. Let cool, then remove from cookie sheet.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: 1. Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to creamed ingredients. 2. Fold in blueberries.
Grease or Pam muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned in 400° oven.
Do not overbake.

title: golden feather cake
directions: Measure ingredients ahead and let sit to room temperature. Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add fat, milk and extract.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use 2 (8-inch) pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
This is good without frosting.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Mix together well.
Wash 2 or 3 cucumbers.
Do not peel, but score down sides.
Add to brine and refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook chopped squash, adding onions, butter, salt and pepper. When squash is tender, drain thoroughly.
Add the can of cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 of the grated Cheddar cheese.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan or a casserole dish.
Spread remainder of grated cheese across the mixture.
Sprinkle can of French's onion on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: cheese straw cookies
directions: Allow Cheddar cheese to soften and mix with margarine and cream. Add salt and flour. Stir in Rice Krispies with fork to keep from breaking up too much. Put on greased cookie sheet with teaspoon; press once with fork. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: skillet beef and rice
directions: In one skillet, brown hamburger.
In large skillet with 3 tablespoons oil, cook celery, green pepper, onion and tomatoes until tender.
Add water to keep them from burning.
Add Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Add meat and rice to vegetables.
Heat until ready to eat.

title: tuna-broccoli casserole
directions: Precook broccoli and put in shallow pan.
Add tuna and cover with diluted mushroom soup.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Add bread crumbs to melted butter and crumble over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nutty noodle clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in a pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover tightly and microwave on High until hot and bubbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir.
Serve over your favorite biscuits.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Place
all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed for 20 seconds.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: russian creme with berries
directions: Stir sugar and vanilla into sour cream until sugar is dissolved.
Top with berries.
Serve chilled.

title: fruit dip(after school snack or appetizer)
directions: Beat 1 envelope of Dream Whip with 1 cup milk until frothy, approximately 2 minutes.
Add pudding, the remaining milk and the almond extract; beat until mixed.
Place in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Cut up available fruit into dipping pieces.
Dip fruit into fruit dip and eat.
Great for after school.
Can refrigerate remaining fruit dip for 3 days.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough in pizza pan.
Cook as directed for cookies.
Let cool.

title: cranberry surprise salad
directions: Dice cranberry sauce into small cubes.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in whipping cream.
Top with nuts (optional). Chill and serve.

title: hawaiian fruity salad
directions: Peel and cut oranges and banana in layers.
Put layer of orange pieces, sprinkle on 1 tablespoon of 10x sugar, put layer of pineapple, layer of banana slices, layer of cherries and layer of coconut.
Start over until you've used all your ingredients. Chill for an hour and serve.

title: fruit yum yum bread
directions: In advance, combine softened cream cheese, sugar and flour. Beat in an egg and grated orange peel; set aside.
Combine the beaten egg, orange juice and water.
Add the bread mix, stirring until moistened.

title: fruited cream cheese dip(to dip fruit in)
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with a beater until creamy. Add next 4 ingredients, mixing until light and fluffy. Spoon into a serving dish. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: spam hot dish
directions: Dice the meat and saute in the oil. Add rice and cook until rice is browned.
Add rest of ingredients except for soy sauce and garlic. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soy sauce and garlic.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° until browned on top.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons of sugar in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°. Remove and pat down; cool.
Beat the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar; stir in Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Dissolve jello in hot water; stir in frozen strawberries.
Cool until partially set, then spoon over the cheese mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: walnut coffee cake
directions: Place yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in a cup.
Scald milk and add butter or margarine.
Cool to lukewarm and add to yeast mixture.

title: oriental chicken stir-fry(makes 4 servings)
directions: In large skillet heat oil over medium heat; add onions, celery, pepper and ginger.
Cook, stirring, until just tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in soup, chicken and soy sauce; heat until hot about 2 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: date chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda. Let stand.

title: cranberry supreme salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Pour into bottom of 1 1/2-quart round mold. Chill until partly set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside.

title: microwave mushroom-stuffed fish rolls
directions: Chop the romaine leaves, mushrooms and butter.
Cook in microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir in marjoram, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Spoon mixture onto each fillet.
Roll fillets and secure with toothpick.
Place into microwave baking dish. Cook on High 3 minutes. Combine cornstarch and bouillon granules.
Stir in 1/2 cup water and egg yolk.
Cook on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, until thick and bubbly.
Stir every 30 seconds. Stir in lemon juice.
Discard toothpicks. Spoon on sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 150 calories.

title: school cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Fill cones 1/2 full.
Set cones in muffin pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Batter will rise like a ice cream cone.
Frost with desired icing.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour gradually until dough is stiff.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut and bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.
If you are in a hurry to bake cookies do not roll them out; instead drop on cookie sheet with a spoon and flatten to right thickness, then bake.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stained glass fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
May be kept in refrigerator several days.
Make at least one day before serving.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat first 4

ingredients 2 minutes. Add 3/4 c. cooking oil, mix well. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and poke holes in hot cake. Mix juice of 2 lemons and 2 cups powdered sugar together and pour over hot cake.

title: orange frost
directions: Combine ingredients in blender; mix until smooth. (Refrigerate what isn't consumed right away, then shake and reblend each serving just before drinking.
It's better when it has just been "revved" in the blender and is foamy.)
Yields 10 to 12 cups.

title: ham quiche
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk with whisk. Add diced ham and onions. Stir well. Pour mixture into pie crust. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven. Allow to set a few minutes before cutting.

title: pasta sauce - don't tell your cardiologist
directions: Slowly heat butter, whipping cream and Gorgonzola cheese until melted.
Serve over your favorite pasta.
Add parmesan cheese to finish.
Serves 4.

title: forgotten dessert
directions: In the morning, whip the Dream Whip and vanilla.
Spread over top of dessert.
Refrigerate.
When serving, add strawberries or blueberries (no sugar).
Serves 10.

title: layer salad(a dessert type salad)
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin, stir.
Add 1 cup cold water and chill until syrupy.
Stir in pineapple, top with sliced banana and sprinkle marshmallows over all.
Chill until firm.

title: steamed chicken with pineapple
directions: With a sharp cleaver, cut the chicken into 2-inch pieces (bone and all), or have the butcher do it.
Heat the oil to 365°.
Fry the chicken in it until browned; drain.
Put chicken pieces in a bowl and the ginger root, green onion, soy sauce, sugar, sherry and salt.
Place bowl on a rack in a pan of boiling water.
Cover and steam for 40 minutes, or until tender.

title: joy's pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Saute the garlic for about 1 minute until golden, stirring constantly. Add chicken strips and saute until white and almost completely cooked. Add the broccoli and saute until crisp-tender, then add the sun-dried tomatoes, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Add the wine, then the broth and butter. Cook for about 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Toss the cooked pasta with the chicken mixture. Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.
Trim with a cluster of green grapes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl at high speed until foamy. Add granulated sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating constantly until sugar is dissolved and whites are glossy and stand in soft peaks.

Beat in vanilla and almond extracts. Sift flour, confectioners sugar and salt together twice. Sift about 1/2 cup flour mixture over egg whites and gently fold in just until flour disappears. Repeat folding in remaining flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time. Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan; gently cut through batter with metal spatula.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly with fingers. Invert cake in pan on funnel or bottle neck.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken seasoned with herbs.
Place in Pyrex dish and add cream soup and chicken broth.
Cover with dressing mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Add onion, celery and green pepper. Saute until tender. Add mushrooms 3 minutes before removing from heat.
Place cut up chicken in large bowl.
Put lemon juice over it. Stir.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Heat chicken soup.
Stir into chicken (don't boil) the Worcestershire sauce.
Combine soup mixture and fold in grated cheese.
Cook noodles. Add to other ingredients.
Makes 2 large casseroles.
If casseroles are in refrigerator before baking, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If baking immediately, bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
If frozen, thaw 2 to 3 hours; bake 1 hour.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk and pour mixture over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour one can instant fruit pie filling over mixture.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over filling.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: six layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer in 8
x
10-inch
pan:
Lettuce, then onion, then peas. Mix mayonnaise and
sugar together and spread on top of peas. Sprinkle on
cheese
and bacon which has been crumbled. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour to make a paste. Add milk and bring to a boil to thicken. Add cheese and seasonings.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes. Slice sausage and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spoon potatoes over sausage and heat in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean or yellow bean soup
directions: Before cooking beans, dice the dill tops smaller.
Cook with fennel seeds (optional).
Put in a large pot.
Cook bacon in small pieces and add to beans.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Add flour and water to make gravy.
Add to beans and cook until beans are tender.
Let cool.
Add sour cream to taste and to thicken.
Serve with rye bread.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Shape into balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place on paper towel to drain grease.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn meal, salt, butter, cream and vanilla.
Blend well before pouring into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prune bars
directions: Mix sugar, oil and apple juice.
Separately mix dry ingredients.
To them, gradually add all other ingredients, mixing just until crumbly.
Pour the mixture into a 9-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes or until resilient to the touch.
Makes 12 bars.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to
After the bread has been toasted, break into pieces
and
place
in
a bowl of warm water to soak. Set aside.
Mix
together
milk,
eggs
and sugar until well blended.
Add
vanilla.
Squeeze the water from the bread and add to the custard mixture.
Add raisins, cherries, pecans and margarine.
Pour
into
9 x 13-inch baking dish;
sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all in large pan and bring to a good boil.
Put in jars and bring pressure to 5 pounds; turn off heat and cool.
You may cook each vegetable separately until tender, especially butter beans, carrots, okra and potatoes, then mix together and can.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/2-inch thick and arrange on pizza pan to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, milk, grated orange rind and 1/4 cup sugar. Spread on crust.
Arrange fruits in circular fashion on cheese mixture.
Mix orange juice, lemon juice, water, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool and pour over fruit. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together until blended the flour, sugar, salt and lard. Mix together and add to flour mixture until well blended the egg, vinegar and water.
Can be kept up to two weeks in refrigerator and can be rerolled and worked without ruining it.
Makes 5 crusts.

title: peanut butter and jelly bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except preserves.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Spread 1/2 the batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread preserves over layer; top with remaining batter.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool completely before serving.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place wings in baking dish.
In bowl, mix together soup mix, jam and Russian dressing.
Pour this over wings.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: elegant toffee
directions: On a foil lined baking sheet, arrange almonds in a single layer over a 12 x 7-inch area.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine butter, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly with clean, dry spoon, until butter is melted. Continue cooking and stirring, 5 to 7 minutes (until mixture is the color of unbleached almonds).
Immediately pour over almonds; do not scrape pan.
Cool completely.
Melt chocolate chips and break toffee into pieces and dip into melted chocolate.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.

title: what-cha-ma-callit
directions: Drain pineapple in bowl, reserving juice.
Use juice and water and enough cornstarch to thicken well.
Bring to a boil; cook a couple of minutes.
Add flavoring.
Refrigerate until real cool. Soften the cream cheese.
Mix with pineapple and powdered sugar. Add cold, thickened juice and Cool Whip.
Line bottom and sides of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Top with graham cracker squares.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: graham-cracker key lime pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in yogurt.
Fold in whipped topping; mix well. Fill pie crust and refrigerate for 12 hours. Garnish with lime slices or mint leaves.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef with seasonings and celery until tender.
Mix with remaining ingredients and cook 1 hour and 30 minutes over medium heat.

title: rice-nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; pack into an oiled 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake for about 50 minutes, until firm. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Unmold and slice.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into hot greased skillet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh fruit punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Mix bananas and fruit juices all together.
Add soda before serving.

title: frankfurter goulash
directions: Fry onions in oil until golden brown.
Cut franks in small rings.
Add to onions.
Add paprika and salt.
Cube potatoes and add tomatoes.
Saute.
Cook 1/2 hour.

title: artichoke yummies
directions: Saute ingredients in a little olive oil.
Add some juice from artichoke jar.
Serve hot in chafing dish or pan with toothpicks.

title: stuffed yellow squash
directions: Boil squash whole until tender.
Cut in half when cool. Remove pulp.
Save and squeeze.
Lay cut halves, emptied, on flat pan.
Mix pulp and all other ingredients together, except for cheese and bacon.
Put mixture in halves.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Heat until hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spicy black beans
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, cook onions in oil until they are lightly browned, about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chicken broth and the remaining ingredients. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat and simmer until beans mash easily (about 4 to 5 hours).

title: treasure filled coffeecake
directions: Combine sugar, orange peel, cinnamon and pecans.
Cut cream cheese into 20 pieces (this is optional).
Separate biscuits; pull each biscuit apart and put piece of cream cheese in center. Reseal biscuit; dip in butter and roll in sugar mixture.
Stand on end in Bundt pan.
Drizzle remaining butter and sugar mixture over top.
Grease Bundt pan with shortening.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool for 1 minute only.
Invert on plate.
Serve warm.

title: caramel apple bread pudding
directions: Put bread in an 8 x 8 microwave-safe dish. Beat 2 eggs in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients to the eggs. Pour over bread. Microwave at 50% power for 14 minutes (or until set). Serve with Caramel Sauce.

title: cheddar cheese crock(makes four 1-cup crocks)
directions: Shred cheese into a large bowl.
Work in butter, mustard and Worcestershire sauce with a wooden spoon to make a very smooth mixture.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap; refrigerate 45 minutes or until mixture firms.
Chop 1 cup of the pecans coarsely and spread on wax paper.
Divide cheese mixture into quarters.
Shape each quarter into a ball on a second piece of wax paper, then roll in chopped nuts.
Pack each cheese ball into a 1 cup crock and garnish with remaining whole pecans.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until gift-giving time.
Plan to give within 2 weeks.

title: icicle pickles
directions: To pickles add salt; pour 1 gallon boiling water over pickles. Soak them in this brine for 1 week, stirring once a day to keep scum from forming.
Drain, cover with fresh boiling water for 24 hours.
Drain.
Add alum the size of a walnut and cover with boiling water and soak 24 hours.
Drain.
Cut pickles into chunks. Heat to boiling vinegar, sugar and pickling spice.
Pour over pickles hot.
Repeat every morning for 4 days, then they are ready to can.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Beat well. Stir in chocolate chips. In another bowl, add flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt. Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat well. Fill muffin tins with 1/3 full with chocolate mixture. Top each with heaping teaspoonful cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with sugar and chopped blanched almonds (if desired). Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken with mushrooms and cheese
directions: In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, melt butter in microwave on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Dip chicken breast halves in butter; coat with mixture of bread crumbs, parsley and paprika.
In same dish, cook chicken, covered, on high 7 to 9 minutes until tender, rotating dish once.
Top each chicken breast with some cheese.
Cover tightly; set aside.

title: salt and flour clay
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth. Bring to a boil. Stir until thick. Put on cookie sheet. Cool and shape.

title: one-serving cheese puff
directions: Cut bread in strips.
Place buttered side down along the sides and on the bottom of a 10-ounce custard dish.
In a bowl, lightly beat the egg.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into custard cup. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until puffy and golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir ingredients to blend.
(No ingredient has been left out. This is all there is to the recipe!)
Drop scant tablespoonfuls of batter into deep hot oil.
Dough will rise and float.
When one side is well browned, flip the hush puppy over and continue cooking until other side is also well browned.
Tear into one to see if it is done.
Very good and simple recipe.

title: chocolate crispies cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, nuts and prunes last.
Cook in well-greased and floured tube pan for about 1 hour at 300°.

title: cinnamon tea ring
directions: Combine chopped walnuts or pecans, sugar and cinnamon into mixture.
Take 1/2 of dough.
Roll into oblong shape; brush with margarine.
Sprinkle mixture over dough.
Roll from long side; seal edges and turn pealed edges down into circle on greased baking sheet.
Cut 2/3 way into ring at 1 1/2-inch intervals. Turn on sides.
Cover.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Insert red or green cherries into cuts, before baking. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cherries. Sppon mixture on non-stick cookie
pan.
Place cherries on top of cookies.
