Bake 8 - 10 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and mushrooms in butter until they are clear.
Season shrimp, then add to vegetables.
Cook on medium heat until shrimp are cooked.
Pour beaten eggs into shrimp and vegetable mixture.
Add rice; stir until rice is coated with egg mixture.
Cover and cook on low heat until eggs are cooked.
(Cook in a 10-inch black iron skillet with cover.)
Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: deep sea punch
directions: Fill a large pitcher halfway with ice. Add all ingredients and stir well. Serve in a chilled glass over ice.

title: mile high meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar with water and boil until thick. Beat egg whites stiff.
Then pour hot syrup into egg whites, continuing to beat.
Pile meringue on pie.
Brown if desired.

title: spinach-mushroom crepes
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Wash mushrooms, cut off stems, chop stems and reserve.
Slice mushrooms thinly.
Prepare cheese mix according to directions.
Reserve 2 cups for topping. When sauce thickens, add cheese, well drained spinach and sliced mushrooms.
Simmer five minutes.

title: mom's chocolate pudding
directions: Combine flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder, salt, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Add milk and mix well. Put 5 tablespoons of cocoa, sugar and hot water in the bottom of 9-inch round or square pan and mix.
Drop batter in pan by large tablespoonfuls.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Wonderful served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: aunt mae's casserole
directions: Cook onion until tender in a small amount of shortening.
Add ground beef and cook until meat separates and changes color.
Add peas and tomatoes and cook 20 minutes.
Cook noodles in salt water.
Alternate layers of noodles and meat mixture.
Add chunks of cheese.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and nuts together. Sprinkle pudding mix over it and toss together.

title: anginetti cream puffs
directions: Prepare the Anginettis by slicing each cookie in half with a small sharp knife.
Mix the Dream Whip with the instructions on box.
Add pineapple, which has been drained, and package of cream cheese, which has been softened.
Place a teaspoon of the mixture between the sliced cookies and this makes about 75 to 80 cream puffs.
Quick and easy for parties.
When not using, place in refrigerator.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and other ingredients. Add beaten egg whites last.
Cook in 2 greased 9-inch loaf pans at 300° until done, approximately 2 hours.
Cake is done when it pulls away from side of pan.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix pineapple, undrained, with dry pudding.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Fold in oranges, Cool Whip and marshmallows. Chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oil; saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and chili powder; cook 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Season to taste.
Pour in greased dish; heat until hot and sprinkle with cheese.
Heat 5 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter; knead in graham crackers, then powdered sugar.
Press in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Melt chocolate, spread over.
Refrigerate for 1 hour; cut in small bars.
Freeze.
Best served chilled.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place in layers in casserole or crock-pot, starting with meat, then onion, celery, carrots and potatoes.
Sprinkle remaining seasonings and soups over layers.
Do not stir.
Cover tightly and do not remove cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours or in crock-pot on high for 5 hours.

title: nut cookies
directions: Beat egg white until frothy; add sugar and beat until egg white melts the sugar.
Add nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300° or until brown.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
Add salt and stir until creamy.
Add the flour, which has been sifted before measuring and mix thoroughly.
Chill.
This will make enough for one 2-crust medium sized pie.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease two pans.
Combine all dry ingredients together in a large bowl. Mix in eggs, milk and oil until well blended.
Add poppy seed, vanilla, almond and butter flavoring; blend well.
Pour mixture into loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: statler brothers' impossible reuben pie no. 9
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a glass 10-inch pie plate (9-inch will not hold all the topping).
Cover bottom of pie plate with crumbled beef.
Lay slices of Swiss cheese (or sprinkle) over beef.
Place sauerkraut over cheese.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Saute garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in onion; set aside.
Cook or steam beans in small amount of water until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine beans with mushroom mixture. Add pepper and dill weed.
Garnish with nuts.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain; reserve fat.
Add equal amount of flour to fat.
Blend in brown sugar and vinegar.
Drain red cabbage; reserve liquid.
Blend cabbage liquid into flour mixture; cook until thickened.
Add cabbage; heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk. Chop onion and beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf in a baking pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Makes 1 quart.
Delicious on boiled shrimp.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Melt margarine and add to noodles with sour cream, cottage cheese and sugar.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish and let stand for at least an hour.
Before baking, beat 3 eggs and 1 cup of milk.
Pour over the noodles and do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until brown.
Add raisins, if desired.

title: kolachy
directions: Mix butter, cheese and egg yolks.
Add flour gradually until well mixed.
Cut into 3 portions.
Roll portion at a time to 1/8-inch and cut 1 1/2-inch squares and put 1/2 teaspoon filling in each square.
Take opposite ends and squeeze together.
Should look like bows.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 15 minutes).
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beet aspic salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water after Jell-O begins to thicken. Add other ingredients and chill.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Drain sweet potatoes; put through ricer until mashed.
Scald milk.
Add vanilla, sugar and butter.
To potatoes add cinnamon, nutmeg and orange juice; stir.
Add milk mixture to potatoes; stir.
Use half of the sweet potato mixture to make a layer on the bottom of your dish, then a layer of marshmallows.
Top with remaining sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° until very hot.
Add a top layer of marshmallows and brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: betty's broccoli casserole
directions: Heat all together.
Stir in 2 packs frozen broccoli or you may use one head of fresh broccoli.
Pour into buttered dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add water gradually.
Stir over heat until thick.
Add egg yolks and butter, then vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400° and for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: so good casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water; rinse and drain.
Meanwhile, brown meat, onion, pepper and mushrooms in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until onion and pepper are done.
Cream the cream cheese with the sour cream.
Add this and cottage cheese with meat mixture and noodles in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: baked cream cheese creamed potatoes
directions: Cream potatoes as usual according to amount of servings needed.
In a large bowl, cream potatoes.
Add cream cheese (8 ounces) and either fresh chopped onion (5) or dried onion flakes to suit taste.
Add parsley and French onion dip.
(For a large bowl of potatoes, use the large size of onion dip.)

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix ingredients for bars in mixing bowl.
Bake in greased and floured cookie sheet or jelly roll pan, 17 x 11 x 1-inch for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: micro chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
In an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch dish, add chicken and coat with sauce.
Marinate 30 minutes or overnight in refrigerator.
Drain off most of the sauce.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 22 minutes, or until tender.
Turn the chicken over and brush with drippings halfway through cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
If using chicken breasts, reduce time.
Watch carefully.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Divide dough into 5 equal parts; shape each into a ball and wrap tightly. Chill.
May be stored up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mini turkey loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Press evenly into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned and no longer pink in center.
Serve with cranberry sauce and garnish, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: spam and cheese delights
directions: Dice Spam and cheese into 1/4-inch cubes.
Dice onion. Combine all ingredients and make into sandwiches.
Grill in sandwich grill.
Makes about 10 sandwiches.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Cook on low heat, stirring often until water is completely absorbed.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 325°
about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Add the cooked broccoli, mushrooms, water chestnuts and chicken broth to the rice mixture. Add seasoning and the grated nonfat cheese.
Spoon into large casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Top with homemade low-fat croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, covered.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: meringue for pies and puddings
directions: Stir cream of tartar into egg whites in large mixing bowl very briefly.
Beat at highest speed until whites stand in firm peaks but are not dry.
Sprinkle tablespoons of sugar on whites slowly, beating continuously until sugar is used.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add garlic, tomatoes, chilies and cheese cubes.
Cook on low for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with nacho chips.
Crock-pot works well.

title: zucchini cheese crisps
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Place mixture in plastic bag.
Dip zucchini slices in butter, then shake gently in bag of crumbs to coat.
Place zucchini on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta seafood salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain and set aside to cool. Dice tomato, onion and green pepper into smallest pieces possible. Dice crab sticks into small cubes.
Add ingredients including spices to cooled spaghetti.
You may add oil at this time and refrigerate or wait until ready to serve.
(Be sure not to put too much oil on salad.)
This dish is best prepared the day before serving.
Great as a side dish.
Can be served cold or at room temperature (very good).

title: layered salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the ingredients in the order they appear in the list.
Cover with foil.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Toss lightly before serving.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions, then drain; put in baking dish.
Add soups and cooked noodles; mix well.
Put two or three slices of cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly covered container.
2 tablespoons equals 1 commercial package.

title: quick and easy taco salad pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Crush corn chips; spread over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top chips with the beef mixture; layer with Mozzarella cheese, tomatoes, lettuce and black olives.
Add sour cream or salsa as desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions and raisins.
Cover with ice water. Drain ice water off no more than 1/2 hour before serving.
Add nuts and bacon.
Pour mixture of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar over broccoli mixture.
Stir well and serve.

title: cheese and wine bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
In saucepan, heat wine, butter, sugar and salt just until warm, stirring constantly until butter almost melts.
Add to dry mixture in mixer bowl. Add eggs.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping side of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in the cheese and enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down. Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Shape into an 8-inch round loaf.
Place in a greased 9-inch pie plate. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 40 minutes.
Bake in a 375° oven about 40 minutes, covering with foil after the first 20 minutes of baking.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick with hot water and place dough in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wipe with tomato sauce.
Layer in meats, adding sauce and cheese between layers.
Top with mushrooms and olives.
Cook at 450° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese; let melt and serve.

title: canned butter corn
directions: Place ingredients in pan with enough boiling water to cover. Bring to boil and while keeping the mixture at boiling temperature, pack loosely into jars.
Process 4 hours in boiling water bath.

title: meat 'n potato skillet supper
directions: In skillet, lightly brown canned luncheon meat and a thinly sliced onion in shortening.
Blend in mushroom soup and milk.
Add potatoes, parsley and a dash of pepper.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Stir.

title: ortega casserole
directions: Put Fritos in large baking pan.
Dampen slightly with water. Cut chiles in strips and put on tortilla chips.

title: cheese and tomato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange croutons in a 9-inch pie plate, then add tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese. In a small bowl with fork, beat remaining ingredients; pour over cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes, or until browned.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits and salt according to directions on grits box.
Add other ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour (until grits are set).
This will fill a 13 x 15-inch casserole dish.
Be sure to season dish with Pam or Crisco or margarine.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue roasted salmon
directions: Marinate salmon in Ziploc bag with pineapple and lemon juices for one hour. Meanwhile, combine brown sugar through cinnamon ingredients. Set aside. Remove salmon from marinade; discard marinade. Place salmon in shallow baking dish, skin side down. Rub dry mixture evenly over salmon. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, celery, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into oval patties 1-inch thick.
Brown on both sides in butter in a skillet.
Combine soup and water, then pour around meat.
Cook slowly in covered skillet for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Heat.
Stir in 1 beaten egg.
When cold, form into croquettes. Roll in bread crumbs, then in beaten egg and back into crumbs. Fry in hot shortening until brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Layer macaroni, tuna and cream of celery soup. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water; add thawed strawberries. Set aside.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Cook and cool separately pasta and Broccoli Normandy.
When cool, combine with dressing.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick mexican spread
directions: Combine cheese and chilies until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips or spread over warm tortillas or corn bread.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins, do not let them become mushy.
Cool. Dice with skins on and place in a large bowl. Fry bacon, reserving 1/3 cup drippings. To potatoes, add bacon, onions, celery, salt, pepper, celery salt and celery seed.
When ready to serve, combine sugar, vinegar, water and well beaten eggs in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Heat reserved bacon drippings in separate pan.
Pour both over potatoes and stir gently. Serve warm.
If desired, prepare potatoes ahead and add dressing just before serving. Serves 16.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Scald milk.
Add Crisco, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Add yeast which was dissolved in warm water.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour gradually.
Beat vigorously.
Cover with foil.
Let rise until double, about 2 hours.
Shape into rolls, kuchens, etc.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake in oven at 350° for large things; bake at 400° for rolls, etc.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot pear juice (add water to liquid from canned pears to make 2 cups).
Gradually add to the cream cheese, blending until smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add mayonnaise and beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in pears and ginger.
Pour into a 1-quart mold and chill until firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: burritos
directions: Prepare ground beef and burrito spices and seasonings according to package directions.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.
Divide meat mixture, beans and cheese among tortillas, leaving bottom 1/3 of tortilla plain.
Fold bottom of tortilla over meat mixture; fold inside toward center and roll up. Serve with shredded lettuce, chopped tomato, picante sauce and sour cream.
Makes 6.

title: caramel-coconut pie
directions: Bake pie shells and let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk; then fold in Cool Whip.
Set mixture in refrigerator to chill.
Meanwhile, toast pecans and coconut with butter in iron skillet.
(Cook on medium and stir constantly until light brown.)

title: chicken dressing
directions: Bake at 425° until done.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo until limp and clean.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and
bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush one half of the Oreos (can use food processor).
Separate the other half and scrape one side clean of the creme filling. Crush separately and add the Oreos with the filling with the first batch.
Melt the butter and add to this mixture.
Make the pudding mix according to directions.
When firm, add the Cool Whip and mix well.
Line the bottom of a plastic flowerpot with cellophane and then with some of the Oreo mixture.
Then add a layer of pudding. Continue to layer until all is finished.
On the top, add the crushed Oreos (without the filling).
This makes the dirt.
Wrap the stem of a flower with cellophane and place in the middle of the Oreos.
Serve with a small gardening spade.

title: picante roll-up
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread 1 tablespoon onto tortilla, roll up and cut into thirds.
Serve cold with picante sauce to dip in.

title: hamburger goo
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add to meat.
Simmer 3 minutes, covered.
Serve on warm buns.
Great on buttered toast.
Serves 6.

title: gramdma's delights pickles
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and put in quart jar.
Boil remaining ingredients and seal immediately.

title: easy turkey quiche
directions: If using stuffing mix, prepare according to package directions.
Press leftover or prepared stuffing into a 9-inch pie plate, forming a crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: beef-and-wild-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown steak in oil in large deep skillet, about 6 minutes. Push steak to side of skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saut for 5 minutes.
Add celery and mushrooms. Saut for 5 minutes.
Add rice and water chestnuts; mix well with steak and vegetables. Add beef broth and soy sauce.
Bring to boil.
Pour into a lightly greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover with foil. Bake for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Fluff rice with fork before serving. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Season to taste the tomato sauce. Slice zucchini 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick.
Grate cheese using 1 1/2- quart casserole, make layers of hamburger, cheese, zucchini and sauce, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: texas slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion and pepper well; salt to taste.
Bring to boil the remaining ingredients; pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: Spray Teflon-coated waffle iron with Pam or lightly oil.
Heat iron on hottest setting.
Blend all ingredients in blender well. Let stand a few minutes.
Pour mixture onto hot iron and close lid.
Bake for 10 minutes without opening lid.
Serve with favorite topping.

title: hazelnut raisin scones
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut butter into the flour mixture until mixture is crumbly.
With a fork, mix the egg and milk together until blended.
Add to the dry ingredients, stirring with the fork.
Mix just until ingredients are blended.
Add nuts and raisins.
With hands gather the dough together into a ball.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board, cut into 8 parts.
Shape each part into a round ball.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
With a sharp knife, slash an x in the center of each scone.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/2 cup mushroom soup, beef, onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
In baking pan firmly shape meat mixture into 8 x 4-inch lof pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Spoon off 2 tablespoons drippings; reserve.
In saucepan over medium heat, heat remaining soup, water and reserved drippings. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Thin sauce with additional water to desired consistency.
Spoon over meat loaf.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: crock-pot turkey breast
directions: Place turkey in crock-pot, add the creamed soup and cook for 4 hours on high or all day on low.
If juice is thin, add a little flour, and cook a little longer.
If you desire, you can add boiled eggs to the juice.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and boil eggplant in salted water for 5 to 10 minutes. Mash.
Add salt and pepper to taste, tomatoes, chopped onion and shredded cheese.
(Reserve enough to sprinkle on top.)
Stir and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with reserved cheese and heat to melt.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Cut pork chops up into bite-size pieces.
Cover bottom of pan with vegetable oil.
Fry pork chops, stirring occasionally.
Chop onion and jalapeno peppers and put in with pork chops when you put in pan.
When pork chops are done, add tomato sauce and mixed vegetables.
Add salt.
Simmer approximately 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: seashell salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In large bowl, combine pasta with salmon, carrots, cucumber, tomatoes, green onions and broccoli florets.

title: date fruit cake
directions: Cut up the dates and add the boiling water and soda; let stand.
Beat the sugar, eggs and oil or shortening.
Add date mixture, candied frut and the walnuts.
Add the flour, salt and vanilla.
Bake in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: haystacks (1)
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips.
Stir until well blended. Remove from heat.
Add noodles and stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan and add onion.
Cook over low heat until the onions are clear but not browned.
Add the mushrooms and increase heat to moderate.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add the flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes longer.
Add the beef stock and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat, add the herbs and simmer the soup for 10 minutes.
Add the cream and simmer for 10 minutes.
Finish the soup by adding the sherry and nutmeg.
Serves 6.

title: savory spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs; add combined milk, butter, onion, parsley flakes, Worcestershire sauce, salt, thyme and nutmeg and mix well. Combine remaining ingredients; add egg mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish. Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 1 hour or at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on 16 x 11-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and salt; drain and add remaining ingredients. Heat in crock-pot.

title: raisin zucchini bread
directions: Finely shred zucchini. Measure 2 cups. Set aside. Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla. Mix well. Combine dry ingredients. Combine with zucchini. Mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes. Turn out on wire rack.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Let dough rise 3 to 4 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out on floured board.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: You will need one 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Let rhubarb set after sprinkling sugar over.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf tin for 1 hour at 350°.
Flour tin if necessary.
Freezes well.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs and lemon juice. Mix well.
Pour into pie crust. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream. Bake 5 minutes longer. Cool, then chill. Top with pie filling.
Makes one 9-inch cheesecake.

title: quick and easy soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dream bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and add ingredients in order. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: fruit punch
directions: In 5-quart punch bowl, mix together all ingredients except the club soda and ice.
Just before serving, add club soda and ice.
Stir.

title: oatmeal pecan pie
directions: Mix dark corn syrup, sugar, oatmeal, coconut, eggs, salt, butter and pecans together.
Pour into pie shell.
This is just a little change to regular Southern Pecan Pie recipes.
Good enough to win a prize at the county fair.

title: sweet and sour fish
directions: In skillet or pan, blend all ingredients, except fish.
Bring to boil and stir until tender, but still crisp, about 10 minutes. Then add fish for 5 minutes more.

title: turkey trizza
directions: Mix water and yeast until yeast is dissolved.
Add Bisquick and knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Place dough in rectangle (15 x 11-inch) pan.
Pinch edge of dough to form edge about 1/2-inch high.
Melt butter in skillet and saute green pepper. Stir in cans of soup and add turkey.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour onto crust.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until crust is brown and filling is hot and bubbly. Onion, broccoli, mushrooms, asparagus and a number of other toppings can be added if desired.

title: paul's (try it you'll like it) cheesy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dice onion into small pieces. Cut cheese into 1-inch squares. Mix eggs and all liquid ingredients in mixing bowl.

Salt and pepper beef. Crush the Zesta saltines. Add all the remaining ingredients and stir until completely mixed. Mixture should be very moist. Add a little more water, if needed. Mound mixture into a deep baking dish (about 2-inches high at center). Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes. Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: rock lobster tails
directions: Thaw lobster tails.
Cut underside membrane around edge and remove.
Grasp tail in both hands; bend backwards toward shell side or crack or insert skewers to keep tail flat.
This will prevent curling.
Combine lemon juice, butter and salt.
Grill tail 5 minutes, flesh side down.
Turn and brush with butter mixture. Grill flesh side up for 10 to 20 minutes or until lobster has lost its transparency and is opaque.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs in a buttered casserole.
Add sugar and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and blend. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Stir 5 times during baking. Cool and stir often. When mixture is cool, form into balls and roll in confectioners sugar. Can be dipped in chocolate, if desired.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix butter, cocoa and milk.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Add powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Add additional milk if too stiff 1 teaspoon at a time.

title: baby bam seasoning
directions: Combine and store in airtight container for up to 3 months.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients and add to tomato soup.
Then add other ingredients in order given.
Keep in refrigerator in a jar and shake well before using.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute hamburger, rice and onion in skillet until meat is browned.
Add salt, coriander, pepper, tomato sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Add enough water to broth to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into meat mixture.
Bring to boil.
Turn into a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes. Uncover.
Top with cheese. Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Dip chicken pieces in milk mixture.
Mix flour, sesame seed, salt and pepper together.
Dip chicken in flour mixture.
Repeat dipping in milk mixture and flour mixture.
Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour butter over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until tender.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all in blender.
Store in jar in refrigerator indefinitely.
Yields about 1 pint.

title: jigglers
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water or juice.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
To unmold, dip pan in warm water about 15 seconds.
Cut into squares or use cookie cutters.
Lift from pan.

title: melt in your mouth cookies
directions: Sift egg yolks very fine into large bowl.
Mix in butter, flour, sugar and vanilla.
Thoroughly mix with hands (warmth from hands helps bind dough).
Roll into 2 1/2 to 2-inch round logs. Freeze or refrigerate until firm.
Slice cookies 1/4-inch thick. Place on cookie sheet.
Using milk or egg white, brush on cookies to help sprinkles stick.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes, until edges only are light golden brown.
Dust with sugar.
Remove carefully.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll each piece until covered in sugar mixture. Place in layers in greased angel food cake pan.
Over each layer, sprinkle some extra sugar mix and nuts.
Heat until bubbly the butter, 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add the applesauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn.
Place in dishpan.
Combine butter, sugar and syrup in a large pan; bring to a boil.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add salt, soda and vanilla.
(It will foam.)
Pour over popcorn and stir to coat.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Turn into molds and congeal.

title: aunt zel's spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, garlic and oil.
Drain grease.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Then, using tomato paste can, add 3 cans of water.
Add 2 teaspoons brown sugar.
Simmer for 3 hours.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Mix 1 cup berries, 1/2 cup sugar, the water, salt and lemon juice.
Put into a blender.
Add cornstarch.
Whirl until blended. Put into small saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Cool to room temperature.
Set aside.

title: borscht soup
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Take meat off bone and put back in broth.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are soft. Add tomatoes and serve.
Very good if a little sour cream is put in each serving.

title: no fat french toast(good morning texas, 1995)
directions: Beat slightly egg whites and add milk and all the other ingredients.
Soak bread in milk mixture for 5 to 10 minutes.
Put into frypan that has been sprayed with fat-free vegetable spray. Cook until "toasted". Top with blackberry topping or apricot/prune topping, or use syrup if you really have to.

title: mama's fried pork chops
directions: Pour flour into a plate.
Salt and pepper chops.
Sprinkle lightly with seasoned salt.
Heat oil in skillet on medium heat until flour sizzles when tested.
Dust chops with flour and fry until golden brown on each side.
Serve with thickening gravy, homemade biscuits and a big slice of red onion!

title: josephine's scalloped corn
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 1-quart sauce dish, oven tested.
One bowl recipe, makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: super delicious chocolate cake
directions: Blend chocolate and honey; cool to lukewarm.
Sift flour once and measure.
Add soda and salt and sift together 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add chocolate and honey mixture and vanilla; blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Add flour alternately with water, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour dressing over and mix in.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add pineapple juice and pineapple.
Add cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix melted margarine and cracker crumbs together and sprinkle over top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Add soup, mayonnaise, chopped pecans, eggs and onion.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon apple bran salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine yogurt, sugar, lemon juice, parsley and salt.
Stir in apples, celery and grapes.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, stir in cereal and spoon onto lettuce leaves.

title: chili dip
directions: Layer in a glass pie pan (do not grease pan) the cream cheese (spread on first), chili without beans and top with cheese.
Heat in microwave for 4 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and oil.
Pour into greased baking pan or muffin tin.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: cherry salad
directions: Blend together the pie filling, milk, pineapple and nuts. Fold in the whipped topping and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chill overnight.
This will serve a lot of people.

title: korean beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate approximately 1 hour.
Quick fry in very hot pan, not using any other oil.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Place 1 tsp. of mixture on wrappers.
Moisten edges with egg yolk.
Fold to form a triangle.
Moisten the two furthermost points with egg yold and fold under.
Deep-fry in hot oil 2-3 minutes, until golden.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer. Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients. Gradually add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in raisins. Drop dough by 2 teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Mix together popped corn and nuts.
In a pan, combine sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
When mixture turns light caramel in color, remove from heat and stir in popcorn and nuts.
Spread out on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Break apart when cool.
Makes about 40 pieces.

title: beer soup
directions: Cook and stir 1/2 cup onion, garlic and Parkay in a large saucepan on medium-high heat until tender.
Reduce to medium-low heat.
Add Velveeta cheese, milk, beer, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted and soup is hot.
Pour into 4 serving bowls; sprinkle with sliced green onions.

title: tuna walnut spread
directions: Combine tuna (well drained), cheese, a little lemon juice, chopped onion, chopped walnuts and pickle relish.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix fresh fruits, celery and nuts together in blender.
Place in colander with canned fruits to drain.
Put all these ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix sugar and jello with boiling water.
Pour over fruit.
Stir and blend well.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: quick lasagne casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add onions and cook lightly.
Add sauces, salt, pepper, sugar and spices.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. While cooking, combine cooked noodles, cottage cheese and sour cream in bowl.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread thinly, soft cream cheese on a pizza pan.
Spread chili sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Top with shrimp, onions and olives.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown chops and put in roaster.
Cover with 3/4 cup of rice.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, thyme, minced onion, oregano and marjoram.
Add 3/4 cup of rice.
Repeat seasonings.
Add 1 bay leaf.
Add 2 cans beef broth and enough water so that broth, plus water, equals 3 cups.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball with strawberry preserves
directions: Grate cheese together. Add onion and mayonnaise.
Mix with hands.
Add pepper and pecans.
Put mixture into a mold with center hole.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove from mold and fill hole with strawberry preserves.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chocolate mocha cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Dissolve soda and cocoa in sour milk and add to mixture.
Work in the flour slowly. Beat 100 times.
Place the mixture in a well-greased, 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in ice cream churn.
Finish filling container with sweet milk.
Churn.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch in water; add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir; boil for 3 minutes.
Store in refrigerator all summer.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix like any fruit cake.
Line pans with foil and bake in a moderate oven 1 hour or until done.
The cake was delicious because I followed the recipe.
The Bible is the same way.
A friend may give you one.
You may read it and think what it says, seems logical or illogical, but you will never know how good it is for your life, unless you try the recipe.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients and put in loaf pan.
Pour ketchup on top and bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Whip cream until just fluffy, not firm.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: squash pickle
directions: Combine
squash,
onion
and bell pepper. Sprinkle with salt. Let stand 1 hour;
drain well.
Combine vinegar, celery seed and mustard
seed
in
a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add the squash mixture
and bring to a hard boil, about 1 minute.	Now it's ready for the jars.

title: fruit cobbler pie
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of pie pan.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and vanilla.
Pour over margarine, then place peach slices evenly over mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Ovens vary, so use caution at first.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, beans, chili powder, cumin, red pepper, hot sauce and garlic powder.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops on both sides in skillet. Cook potatoes in 1 cup of boiling water for 15 minutes.
Drain. Spoon into a lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup of onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with chops and remaining onions.
Pour soup evenly all over.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 30 minutes longer or until meat is tender.

title: scalloped potatoes au gratin
directions: Slice potatoes and onions.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onions and cheese sauce, sprinkling on salt and basil.
Cover with NUT MILK.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spicy oven-barbecued chicken(yields 6 servings)
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Baste chicken with sauce and continue baking uncovered an additional 30 minutes or until tender.

title: french rice
directions: Combine soup and butter.
Stir. Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts. Save liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to make 1 1/3 cups.
Add mushrooms, chestnuts, liquid and rice to soup.
Stir and pour into greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° covered for 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts and dried beef
directions: Place dried beef in bottom of baking dish.
Wrap chicken breasts in bacon strips and place on beef.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: grilled veggies
directions: Cut up veggies into small, bite-size pieces.
Be sure potatoes are sliced thin.
Prepare in aluminum foil large enough to fold over to form a "bag."
Add other ingredients and season to taste. Put on a hot grill and cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Turn over once during cooking.
Serves 4.

title: wild rice-chicken supreme(good enough for company, brunch or dinner)
directions: Prepare rice and seasoning packets according to directions. Melt the butter in a large saucepan.
Add onions; cook on low until tender.
Stir in the flour, salt, pepper, half and half and chicken broth.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in chicken, pimentos, parsley, almonds and cooked rice.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa snack cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in a 9 x 9-inch microwave-safe dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir into flour mixture until well blended.
Microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn twice, until pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: pistachio bars
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Mix together melted
margarine, 3 Tbsp. sugar and flour put in a 9 by 13 inch cake pan; bake for 15 minutes. Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and
1/2 of cool whip; spread over cooled crust.
Mix with a mixer, pudding and milk, blend until set. Spread over cream cheese layer; spread remaining cool whip on top. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: deep fried mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and dry thoroughly on towel.
Small mushrooms may be left whole; large ones should be cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add any fresh fruit you desire as flavor.
Add vanilla to taste.

title: breakfast brunch casserole
directions: Place 8 slices of bread flat in a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish. Place a slice of meat and a slice of cheese on each piece of bread.
Then place another slice of bread on top of each.

title: chicken cornbread casserole
directions: Combine cornbread, peppers, onions and celery.
Mix well. Place half mixture in 2-quart baking dish.
Spread chicken over cornbread layer.
Combine soup and broth and pour over chicken. Place remaining cornbread mixture and press down.
Set aside for 20 minutes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese with ham and salsa
directions: Cook macaroni in large pot 10 to 12 minutes until tender. Drain and return to pot.
Add cheese sauce.

title: easy chicken wings(microwave)
directions: Cook margarine, onion, chili powder, covered on high 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in honey, mustard, salt and hot sauce.
Pour over chicken wings and cook on high until tender.

title: ollie's key lime-chocolate pie(in honor of "abercrombie")
directions: Combine crushed cookies, coconut and butter.
Spread evenly in a 9-inch pie plate.
Press onto bottom and up sides to form a firm, even crust.
Bake in a 375°
oven about 8 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Great prepared ahead overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put first four ingredients in saucepan at low heat.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from stove.
Then add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Spread on cookie sheet and chill.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour half in each pie shell and bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add oleo, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Mix with mixture.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at temperature on package and cool completely.
Mix together thoroughly cream cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled dough.
Sprinkle on any variety of the following:
red and green pepper, yellow pepper, black olives, shaved carrots, tomatoes, broccoli, cauliflower, celery, radishes or cucumbers.
Cut into 1-inch squares and chill.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously grease a roasting pan with Crisco, then sprinkle liberally with flour.
I use approximately 1/4 cup of flour.
Place the rack in the pan.
The Crisco and flour will brown and combine with the pan drippings to make a brown gravy. Remove excess fat and fell from lamb.
(The fell is the paper like membrane covering the meat.)
Cut small slits in the lamb and insert slivers of garlic into the meat.
Rub the meat with freshly ground pepper, rosemary and olive oil. Spread the mustard generously over the surface of the meat.
Place the lamb on the rack in the roasting pan.
Place leg of lamb in oven and immediately reduce heat to 325°.
Roast approximately 30 minutes per pound.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine butter, garlic, water and cheese in a double boiler and cook 10 minutes over hot water.
Mix flour, mustard and vinegar; stir milk into this.
Add salt and pepper.
When mixed, add slowly to cheese mixture and cook until quite thick.
Put crabmeat in a buttered baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over it and top with bread crumbs.
Top with tomato and bacon.
Cover. Bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes.
Just before serving, uncover and brown bacon.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate goodie
directions: Mix graham crumbs, pecans and margarine and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down.

title: cheesy steak and rice
directions: Brown steak, onion and pepper until tender.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Mix in 1 cup water with onion soup.
Add to steak mixture.
Allow to reduce.
Cook rice.
Pour steak mixture over rice.
Add cheese to top.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt butter and saute onion until clear.
Add soup, mushrooms (with liquid) and cheese until it melts.
Add cooked broccoli; serve hot with your favorite crackers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Then mix in meat.
Shape into a loaf.
Cover with ketchup; score with a knife to make indentations at a slant.
Sprinkle with chili powder.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak beans for several hours.
Parboil for 20 minutes. Cut onions in small pieces and brown with meat.
Put in casserole and add 2 cups of juice drained from the beans.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: carrots marinade
directions: Cook carrots about 20 minutes.
In separate pan, bring to a boil:
tomato soup, sugar, dry mustard, salt, vinegar and cooking oil.
Slice bell pepper and onion.
Layer carrots on bottom; alternate with pepper and onion layers.
Pour on liquid.
Chill 12 hours before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks or more.

title: microwave peanut brittle(makes about 1 pound)
directions: Grease baking sheet heavily.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 3-quart casserole.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High (100%) until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses well.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt; mix well.
Make 1 big or 2 small balls, then roll in chopped pecans.

title: play dough
directions: *Alum is the secret ingredient that helps to preserve this dough from molding.

title: vidalia onion chips
directions: Separate each wedge into chips.
Place in ice water.
Beat together the milk and egg.
Remove chips from water; dip in flour, then egg mixture.
Dip in bread crumbs and seasoning.
Fry in hot oil until brown; drain.

title: crab meat topper
directions: In a small bowl, blend cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir in crab meat. Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve as a spread with Ritz crackers.

title: theresa shea's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Blend into creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Turn into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: scotland's american chop chuey
directions: Cook ground meat and add stewed tomatoes, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add seasoning to taste to the cooked macaroni.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In a large bowl, combine cucumbers, onions, salt and garlic. Stir in a large amount of cracked ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Remove garlic.
In a large kettle, combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, turmeric and celery seed.
Add drained mixture. Bring to a boil.
Pack cucumber mixture and liquid into hot, sterilized pint jars, leaving a 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids. Process 10 minutes.
Makes 8 pints.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook whole carrots until just tender, then slice in lengthwise strips.
Arrange carrots in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots. Top with 1/4 cup bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle top with paprika or parsley. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad cake
directions: Drain fruits and reserve juice.
Together with apple chunks, spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle jello evenly over fruit; then sprinkle dry cake mix.
Drizzle melted margarine and juice evenly over cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve alone or with ice cream or sherbet.

title: sri lankan chicken curry
directions: Combine lemon juice with curry powder, red pepper and ginger; set aside.
Melt butter in stock pot.
Add all onions and garlic to saute.
Add lemon juice-spice mixture.
Saute until onions are soft.
(At any point, you can add more curry powder or red pepper.)

title: veggie-nut casserole
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients together well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Sprinkle on top and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Melt margarine. Add flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar. Spread in an 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes until bubbling. Beat sugar, eggs, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons flour and pour over hot crust. Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 5 to 6 minutes until center is firm. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cool completely before cutting.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: herring antipasto
directions: Drain and cut herring into small pieces.
Place in bowl.
Add green pepper, onions, olives and artichokes.
Add chili sauce. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Serve plain or with crackers or cocktail bread.
This is very colorful in a clear glass bowl.

title: pineapple cranberry mold
directions: Drain crushed pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine reserved juice with 3/4 cup pineapple juice in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Break up cranberry sauce and add to gelatin.
Stir in Port wine or cranberry juice.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened.
Add crushed pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate; garnish with sliced pineapple.
Serves 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together with hands.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg, flour and cinnamon into large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, banana, oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie pan. Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kingdom cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill dough 1 hour.
Roll out dough and cut in heart shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly golden.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, almonds, chicken soup, cooked rice, lemon juice, salt, pepper and eggs.
Toss gently.

title: watergate cake
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Grease	a
Bundt pan.
In large bowl, combine cake
mix,	pudding,
salad
oil, eggs and soda; beat well.
Fold in chocolate pieces.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple dip
directions: Put both ingredients into bowl.
Blend on medium speed for five minutes, until well blended.
Cut apples into wedges.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter till lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Add broth and worcestershire.
Bring to boiling.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle toast with cheese; place under broiler till cheese is lightly browned.
Pour soup in bowls and float toast slices atop.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of water.
Add 2 cups of liquid and the pineapple juice.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: chocolate covered peanut clusters
directions: Melt in large pan in oven at 170°.
Stir together well.
Add 2 pounds dry roasted, salted peanuts.
Stir again and drop on wax paper.

title: five minute peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in pan over low heat and then stir in peanut butter.

title: our favorite devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat yolks; add water and extract and blend.
Gradually add yolk mixture to chocolate mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, blending well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Turn into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans or one greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake layers or loaf in moderate oven at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly. Turn out on cooling rack.
Yields two 9-inch layers or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: quick graham cracker squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large bowl and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares, cool and serve.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Cover with lime and water solution (might have to add water to make it cover).
Soak 24 hours.
Rinse well. Cover with fresh cold water.
Soak 3 hours longer.
(This removes the excess lime.)
Drain.
Cover with vinegar, sugar and spices. Soak overnight.
Be sure cucumbers are covered.
In morning put on stove and boil until clear.
Pack and seal.
These stay crisp.
Can add green food coloring.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Roll chicken in batter.
Fry in hot cooking oil until golden brown.
Drain.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with fruits of your choice.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Roll 2/3 of pie crust to fit an 8-inch or 9-inch pie pan. Arrange apple slices in crust and sprinkle tapioca on top of apples, then sprinkle Sweet 'N Low and cinnamon on top.
Roll out remaining pie crust, perforating the top and arrange over apples. Crimp edges securely, moistening with a little water, if necessary. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
One sixth of pie is 227 calories.

title: crispy italian bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine olive oil or butter or margarine and bread crumbs.
Spread cut surfaces of bread with crumb mixture.
Switch oven to broil.
Broil bread 3 inches from heat source for one minute or until surface is bubbly and lightly browned.
Slice and serve immediately.
Makes 16 (2-inch) slices.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: Make white sauce by melting butter and adding flour, seasoning and stirring in milk.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.
Add ham, spaghetti, parsley and mushrooms. Pour into a casserole and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cooked turkey or chicken may be used in place of ham.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding rhubarb last.
Pour equally into 2 bread pans sprayed with Pam.
Don't clean out bowl with spatula yet!

title: chili beans
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: oven brown rice
directions: Dice onion and saute in butter in a small sauce pan, set aside. In a 9 x 13 dish, combine uncooked rice and beef consomme. Stir in sauteed onion. Bake for 1 hr. in a 400° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften spread and cheese.
Mix all together with mixer. Cool in	refrigerator.
Roll
into
ball.
Roll in 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans and parsley.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and butter. Press 3/4 into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pudding and milk. Beat 1 minute.
Add softened ice cream and beat until smooth.
Pour on crumbs and let set 1 hour.
Spread on Cool Whip, crushed candy bars and mix to crumbs and sprinkle on top.

title: good chicken
directions: Lay chicken in baking pan.
Cover each piece with cheese. Dilute soup with wine and pour over top.
Melt margarine and toss with stuffing and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 2.
To serve more, double topping after six.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Add salt, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add beans.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternating, add dry ingredients with milk and butter mixture.
Beat egg white until fluffy and fold into batter. Add blueberries.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, chili powder, shortening and bell pepper all together.
Add tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste. Place in baking dish.
Top with uncooked rice.
Add water.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Mix in vanilla.
Mix cocoa and confectioners sugar in bowl.
Add
cheese mixture to cocoa and mix quickly.
Spread in a 9 x 13 inch dish.
Pat pecans over top.
Yield: 3 lb.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Whip butter.
Add sugar (1 cup at a time).
Mix well with mixer.
Add eggs (2 at a time).
Sift flour; add 1 cup at a time. Add vanilla and lemon flavor and mix well.
Add 7-Up and stir well, then mix for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and chill until serving.
For dips for vegetable platter, add 16 ounces of sour cream to thicken.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk and shortening.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
While warm, spoon cake into dessert dishes and spoon sauce over each serving. If desired, garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: meat and vegetable loaf
directions: Put raw vegetables through food chopper.
Mix all ingredients together by hand then press into desired form.
Bake at 375° to desired doneness.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and water. Allow to stand 5 minutes. Add buttermilk. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Stir in dates and nuts. Mix well. Add dry ingredients. Stir until blended. Place in greased muffin tins. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°. Batter may be stored in covered container in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: creamsicle
directions: In saucepan, mix water, jello and pudding.
Bring to a boil. Refrigerate overnight.
With electric mixer, beat mixture.
The next day, add Cool Whip and drained oranges.
Whip until creamy. Refrigerate.

title: chicken swiss stuffing bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9x13 pan.
Place a slice of cheese on top of each breast.
Mix the sour cream, soup and stuffing. Pour on top of chicken.
Top with melted butter and sprinkle with additional stuffing.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add mushroom soup and garlic cheese.
Bring to a boil; add red pepper to taste.
Add sauce to vegetables in covered casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cornbread sausage dressing with apples and pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Cook sausage, onion and celery in skillet until sausage is brown and vegetables are tender.
In large mixing bowl, combine sausage and vegetable mixture with remaining ingredients.
Stir gently.
Spoon into prepared baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion, salt, garlic and pepper.
Shape mixture into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: uncle otto sparkman's punch
directions: Place the sugar cubes in a large bowl.
Pour over the hot tea; stir well.
Add the lemon juice, peach brandy, rum and bourbon; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, transfer the mixture to a punch bowl and add the club soda.
Yields 30 servings.

title: ricotta cheese pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour mixture onto a lightly greased, preheated grill in 2-inch rounds over a medium-low heat.
Turn cakes when small bubbles form on surface. Serve hot, dusted with powdered sugar or maple syrup.
Also good with strawberry or raspberry preserves.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: cheese puff balls
directions: Mix dough well, until smooth.
Make balls with a teaspoon and drop them into frying oil, not too hot so as not to burn.
Cook for 5 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter well and place in pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs; pour over cake mix.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Spread in buttered 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange asparagus spears over rice.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and half of cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over rice, asparagus and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Serve.

title: mustard barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients except Worcestershire sauce, which is added as the boiled ingredients are removed from heat. Mix!
Excellent with chicken.
Brush sauce onto individual pieces or 1/2 chicken and cook slowly over open charcoal already glowing hot.
Turn frequently and re-apply sauce and after each turn.
Cook until charcoal turns to ash.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour one cup at a time; mix after each addition.
Divide dough into 2 balls.
Roll each ball out on a floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet on top rack of oven for 6 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar while hot.

title: caper's dip
directions: Arrange cling peach halves in a baking dish.
Put a heaping spoonful of mincemeat with brandy on each one.
Heat for about 15 to 20 minutes.
This can be served hot or room temperature.
Allow one peach half per person.

title: candy bar squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed, beat margarine and sugars together until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt. Reserve 1/2 cup of chopped candy.
Stir remaining candy into batter.
Spread mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter remaining 1/2 candy on top of batter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until browned.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: penny salad
directions: Slice carrots into coins.
Cook carrots until firm.
Drain. Mix remaining ingredients in small saucepan and bring to boil. Cook 2 minutes more and pour over drained carrots while still hot. Place in covered container and store in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Layer banana, grapes and oranges in serving bowl or 6 dessert dishes.
Sprinkle coconut between layers.
Sprinkle coconut on top layer.
Drizzle with orange juice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wonderful walnut (or pecan) pie
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter or margarine in double boiler. Stir in sugar, eggs, salt, syrup and cream, and cook for 5 minutes over hot, NOT boiling water.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into piecrust shell and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and arrange about 7 walnut or pecan halves on top and bake 15 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: italian bean soup(with pasta)
directions: Place beans in a small pot.
Cover with 2 cups boiling water and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans and set aside. In a 5 - 6 quart pot heat olive oil.
Cook the carrots, celery, and onion until onion is soft.
Mix in garlic, parsley, and pepperoni.
Add ham chunks, tomatoes with liquid, bay leaf, beans, and 6 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer until beans are tender about 1 1/2 -2 hours. Remove bay leaf.
Remove 1 cup of bean mix and puree in a blender with a little of the liquid.
Add back to the soup along with pasta. Bring to a boil.
Cook uncovered until the pasta is tender, 12 - 15 minutes.
Season to taste with salt.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together refried beans and taco sauce.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dice onion on top.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Spread on top of beans and onion. Chop lettuce and put on other layers.
Shred cheese and spread on top.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well after each.
Reserve 1 cup cream cheese mixture; add pumpkin, remaining sugar and spices to remaining cream cheese mixture.
Layer 1/2 pumpkin and half cream cheese mixture over crust; repeat layers.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: homemade paste
directions: Mix flour with water until smooth.
Store in covered container.
For more durable paste, add 1/2 cup flour to 1 cup boiling water.
Stir over low heat until thick and shiny.

title: warm cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg yolks, butter and sugar until pale yellow.
Add cocoa and cinnamon.
Moisten bread crumbs with cherry juice, add to dough with almonds.
Beat egg whites with sugar until soft peaks appear.
Mix carefully into dough, alternately with cherries.
Bake in a buttered 10-inch spring-form pan.
After first 10 minutes, turn oven down to 375° and bake 50 minutes more.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add marshmallows and let melt.
Stir in salt and pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cottage cheese, whipped cream and nuts.
Turn into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: salmon steaks in orange honey marinade
directions: Marinate 1 hour.
Drain and reserve.
Grill 5 minutes.
Turn and marinate.
Grill 5 more minutes.

title: special k treats
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a full boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and cereal. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Pour over the cereal mixture.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover.
Chill several hours.
Garnish with croutons, if desired.

title: tzatziki
directions: Mix altogether.
Keep refrigerated at least 1 hour.
Great vegetable dip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour milk and broth over all in large glass dish.
Mix margarine and bread crumbs; spread over top. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: fruity dessert cups
directions: Combine pineapple, grapes and kiwi fruit.
Cover. Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, spoon fruit mixture into individual dessert dishes.
Top with ice cream; drizzle with syrup.
Make 4 servings.

title: chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and egg in mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly in 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: barbecued chicken sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in small pan and bring to a boil.
Place chicken in deep dish and pour sauce over chicken.
Let marinate a couple of hours.
Grill chicken on grill for about 1 hour using sauce to baste.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together sour cream, hash browns, onion, soup and cheese. Place in large baking dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing and melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish crescents
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, walnuts and vanilla. Shape into crescents.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: carolina gumbo
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in a Dutch oven, stirring until beef crumbles. Drain, rinse with hot water and return to Dutch oven. Stir in corn and next 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice. Sprinkle with hot sauce, if desired. Yield: 1 1/2 quarts.

title: dirty rice
directions: Parboil livers and gizzards in 3 cups water.
Keep stock. Simmer ground meat in shortening for 20 minutes. Add livers, gizzards, chopped vegetables and seasonings.
Cook 20 more minutes. Add 2 cups stock and simmer for 20 minutes. Add and mix in rice when ready to serve. Serves 12.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Combine flours, oats and soda; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and lemon peel. Beat well.
Stir in vegetable or fruit.
Add flour mixture, a third at a time, beating on low speed until combined.
Stir in walnuts.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix 1 teaspoon sugar in warm water; let dissolve and add yeast.
Put milk (lukewarm) in bowl.
Add water and yeast mixture. Add 2 tablespoons sugar, shortening, salt and enough flour to make stiff batter.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Knead, cut into rolls and let rise until double in bulk.
Cook.

title: pop up bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and salt until warm (120° to 130°), stirring to blend.
Add to flour mixture along with eggs and cheese.
Beat with an electric mixer or by hand until batter is smooth.
Using a spoon, mix in the remaining flour (batter will be stiff).
Divide batter and spoon into two well-greased coffee cans.
Cover with plastic lids.
Let rise in a warm place until batter is 1/4 to 1/2-inch below plastic lids, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove lids and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing.
Grated cheese may be omitted.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and sour cream, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon, mixing well. Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Cover and chill overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tests done.

title: auntie's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together in one bowl.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: moravian chicken pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add just enough ice water to moisten flour mixture. Divide dough in half.
Roll each half out.
Place crust into bottom of 9-inch pie pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with crushed pineapple and juice until pudding is dissolved. Add Cool Whip.
Fold in miniature marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: chinese egg drop soup
directions: Start broth to boil and add onions. Cook on medium heat until onions are tender. Beat eggs well and drizzle by spoon into broth, stirring often, until all egg is used. Mix a small amount of water and flour or cornstarch in a bowl in order to thicken soup. Add to soup and stir well. Thicken more if desired. Salt and pepper as you cook to desired taste. Serve and eat with chow mein noodles.

title: sausage cake
directions: In mixing bowl combine meat and sugars and stir until mixture is well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.
On a piece of waxed paper, sift flour, ginger, baking powder and spices.
Stir baking soda into coffee.
Add flour mixture and coffee alternately to meat mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well and dry raisins in cloth.
Fold raisins and walnuts into cake batter. Turn batter into well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until done.
Cool 15 minutes in pan before turning out.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Beat until whipped together, then dip your fruit.

title: doritos chicken casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Use 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put layer of Doritos
on
bottom;
add
layer of chicken soup mixture, then cheese.
Continue
to
layer
but the last layer is Doritos and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 20.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Use 4 tea bags for a 2 liter jar, 6 tea bags for a 3 liter jar or 8 tea bags for a 1 gallon jar.

title: ice cream
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar; add flour and eggs slowly, stirring until thickened.
Cool.
Add cream, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Cool and freeze.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour,
margarine and powdered sugar thoroughly.
Press evenly in bottom of an 8 or 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini and cheese casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp. Take out of pan and set aside.
In skillet, melt margarine. Saute zucchini and onion until tender. Drain well. Put zucchini and onion back in the skillet.
Put water and cheese. Top with crushed bacon.
Turn down heat. Cover and cook until cheese melts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix ground orange
rind
and cranberries with sugar and let stand.
Soften 2 packages Knox gelatine in 1 1/2 cups cold water with 1 1/2
cups
hot orange juice (including previously used orange).
Add pinch of salt
and
the 1 cup of finely cut celery and nuts.
Refrigerate until used.

title: bran muffins(triple recipe)
directions: MIX IN ORDER. Put in large covered bowl. Refrigerate.
Batter keeps up to 5 weeks. Do not restir. Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes. Makes several dozen.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook shells in salted boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Dice half Mozzarella cheese; slice the rest.
In large skillet, brown ground round and sausage and drain off grease.
Add bread crumbs, milk, parsley, egg and diced Mozzarella cheese to the meat and mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Fill cooked shells with meat mixture.
Place half tomato sauce in a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Place stuffed shells in dish; top with remaining sauce and sliced Mozzarella. Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: flan
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Using blender, blend eggs and vanilla. Gradually stir in the milk.
Pour into 6-ounce custard cups.* Place cups in baking pan,
13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Pour very hot water into pan to within 1/2-inch of the top of cups.
Bake for 2 hours, until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean. Remove from water.
Turn them upside down. Serve warm or cold.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper with garlic salt in margarine in skillet.
Combine soup, broth and tomatoes in bowl; mix well. Layer half the Tostados, soup mixture, chicken and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: ricotta biscuits (cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
With a wooden spoon, cream eggs and sugar. Stir in oil; mix in extract.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in almonds and cranberries.

title: health bread
