directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, margarine, molasses, salt, honey, brown sugar and eggs slightly beaten.
Blend well. Add wheat germ, soybean flour and dry onion mix.
Add 2 cups flour and beat.
Then add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover, let rise in warm place (80 to 85°) until double in bulk, about 1 hour. Punch down, divide in 3 parts, shape in loaves.
Place in pans. Cover and let raise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.
Cool on wire racks.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and let simmer on low heat for about 15 minutes.
Green pepper and onion don't have to be cooked thoroughly.
You can alter amounts of ketchup, mustard and brown sugar to suit your taste buds.
Great for serving at parties, etc.

title: noodles
directions: Combine egg, salt and milk.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll very thin on floured surface.
Let stand 20 minutes. Roll up and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Spread out to dry 2 hours. Drop into boiling broth and cook 10 minutes. I cut mine 1-inch thick and cook 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: pork tenderloins
directions: Saute thinly sliced pork in 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Remove. Saute onions and pepper.
Add spices.
Mix tomatoes in with the spices, onions and pepper.
Put pork in this sauce and simmer about 20 or so minutes.
Pour over fresh angel hair pasta. Delicious!!!!

title: ooey gooey pecan bars
directions: Mix 1 stick melted butter, cake mix and 1 egg. Spread into greased 9 X 13 pan. Mix remaining ingredients pour over top. Bake at 350° for 40 min. Cover with foil, bake 10 more minutes. Let cool.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato filling
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until done.
Saute onion in butter until soft and yellow.
Drain potatoes and mash, using 3/4 cup milk.
Mix in sauteed onion and butter, bread, egg, flour, etc. Season to taste.
Thin with remaining milk.
Beat or mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Butter top for a brown crisp crust.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Press into 9-inch spring form pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal crispies(cookies)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Dip with ice cream dipper (small one) or drop from spoon or may be rolled in waxed paper and put in refrigerator for 1 or 2 hours or overnight, then sliced.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 350°
oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour. Cool completely before removing from pans.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Beat eggs, cream and spices with mixer until thoroughly mixed. Crumble bacon and add to mix with cheese and vegetable or mushrooms.
Stir well.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake at least 3 more minutes until firm and set.

title: tuna salsa dip or sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except tuna.
When ingredients are blended together, fold in tuna.
Serve with nachos or chips.
Also can be used as sandwich filling.

title: angel hash
directions: Mix well and chill 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: easy manicotti with cheese
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce and water in saucepan to boiling; reduce heat and keep warm.
Mix together Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into uncooked manicotti.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Place 1/3 cooked rigatoni in crock-pot.
Add 1/3 meat, 1/3 pizza sauce, 1/3 optional ingredients and 1/3 cheese.
Layer remaining ingredients in same order.
Do not stir.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Center Filling (goes between cake):
Mix 5 tablespoons plain flour and 1 cup milk.
Cook until it gets real thick and then let it cool.

title: roast beef
directions: Wrap beef in foil and pour mixture over beef.
Seal and bake at 350° for about 3 hours.

title: egg rolls
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, carrots, soy sauce and spice. Drain grease. Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture on each egg roll wrapper, fold sides and then roll. Brush on beaten egg or water to seal. Fry in oil until golden brown. Serve alone, with sweet and sour sauce, or with hot mustard. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add a pinch of salt.
Fold in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased foil lined cookie sheet and place in preheated oven. Turn oven off, close door and leave cookies inside for about 8 hours.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: frozen peanut pops
directions: In mixing bowl, beat ice cream until soft and beat in peanut butter alternately with milk.
Makes about 3 cups.
Place 1 tablespoon chopped peanuts in bottom of a 5 ounce paper cup. Spread 1 tablespoon fudge over nuts and spoon in 1/4 cup peanut butter ice cream.
Repeat, ending with ice cream.
Insert wooden stick in center and freeze.
To serve, remove paper cup.
Makes about 6 (5 ounce) cups.

title: rosemary's fruit cloud
directions: Drain and reserve juice from fruit cocktail.
Combine juice, water and jello.
Heat until dissolved.
Fold in topping, fruit cocktail, cottage cheese and nuts.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8.

title: 6 week bran muffin
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in cereal, milk and raisins together.
Let stand for 2 minutes, then add eggs and oil. Add flour mixture and stir only until all is combined.
Spray Pam in muffin tray and fill them with batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Keep remainder of batter covered in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Make more when needed.

title: striped apple delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot apple juice; add 1 1/2 cups of applesauce, bananas and celery.
Pour half of the mixture into a 1-quart dish or mold.
Chill 30 minutes.
Leave other half of gelatin mixture at room temperature.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup applesauce and sour cream; spread over chilled gelatin.
Pour remaining gelatin over sour cream mixture.
Chill until firm. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pizza
directions: Mix 1/2 cake mix as directed on box, but add 2 ripe bananas, mashed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch
pan, greased.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.
Mix a large box of Jell-O as directed. Chill until it just begins to set.
Slice bananas on cool cake. Pour Jell-O over bananas and cake.
Put in refrigerator until Jell-O is set.
Serve or decorate with whipped cream!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sprinkle sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon on sliced peaches.
Toss to mix. Place in shallow casserole dish. Mix sugar, flour and egg to crumb like texture.
Pour over peaches. Melt margarine or butter over the crumb topping. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until top slightly turns brown and crusty.

title: deer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into long roll.
Wrap in foil and seal.
Set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: heath cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix.
While the cake is still warm, punch holes over cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk all over cake, then add ice cream topping on top.
Let cake cool, then spread container of Cool Whip on top and put 6 crumbled Heath candy bars on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet and sour sauce(serves 6)
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water and save.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and cook over low heat for 15 minutes, then heat to a low boil and add cornstarch to thicken.
Take off heat and serve with chicken, pork or vegetables.

title: chris' magnificent muffins
directions: Sift flour.
In another bowl, combine milk, egg and oil.
Add sugar to flour, then add liquid ingredients to sugar and flour. Mix lightly.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full of batter.
Bake in 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites almost stiff.
Slowly add sugar, continue beating until very stiff.
Slowly fold in nuts and chips.
Drop onto foil-lined cookie sheet and place in oven. Turn off heat immediately and "forget" about the cookies for hours or overnight.
(These are good to make at night, then go to bed and "forget them"!)

title: edna's jam cake
directions: Bake 4 layers in 350° oven until done.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Mix pizza sauce and drained hamburger meat.
Alternate layers of ingredients with pepperoni and cheese, ending with cheese on top. Cook 2 hours on low heat in crock-pot.

title: carrot sandwich spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese with mayonnaise. Add remaining ingredients. Store in refrigerator until ready to use on sandwiches or crackers.

title: no bake oatmeal candy
directions: Boil butter, milk, sugar and cocoa for 3 minutes, then add vanilla and oatmeal.
Then pour into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Let harden, then cut and enjoy.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Add peanut butter, graham crackers, vanilla and confectioners sugar to butter or margarine.
Form into balls and refrigerate until cold.
Then dip into candy melts and put on wax paper.
Candy melts can be purchased at Blake's Hardware.
Dipping spoon can also be purchased at Blake's Hardware.
One bag of candy melts is not enough to dip all peanut butter balls.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 450° for one hour.
Let cool.
Slice potatoes in half, scoop out potato with spoon and leave skin empty.
Mix the potato with all the other ingredients, mash until no lumps, then pour back into skins.
Top potatoes with 1/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: barbecued spare ribs(crock-pot)
directions: Place spareribs on rack in baking pan in 400° oven for 15 minutes; turn and brown other side 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain fat and put ribs in slow cooker.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover.
Cook 6 to 8 hours.

title: chili
directions: Put hamburger, canned tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, ketchup, salt and pepper to taste and water in pan.
Start on high; heat for 5 to 10 minutes, then turn heat down on low and cook for 2 hours, until done.
Stir once in a while, not to stick.

title: grandma's apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; roll 1/2 of dough out for crust. Roll 1/2 of dough for decorative top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soups and margarine together; add rice.
When warm, pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan or casserole.
Put chicken pieces on top.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/4 hours.

title: butter rolls
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
In another bowl, put flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut each biscuit into halves.
Dip in butter, then in flour mixture.
Place and layer in baking pan. Sprinkle rest of leftover flour mixture over biscuits and pour leftover butter on top.
Boil enough water to pour over all to about 3/4 inch of top of pan.
Bake at 325° until brown and done.

title: five-flavor pound cake
directions: Grease large pound cake pan.
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: salad south pacific
directions: Combine pineapple, rice, celery and raisins.
Toss lightly. Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over rice mixture and toss.
Cover and chill.
Serve in a bowl lined with crisp salad greens, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix by hand sugar, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt.
Put butter in the middle of mixture.
Place in microwave on High for 2 minutes and 15 seconds.
Take out and stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place it into the refrigerator.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in air tight container.	To serve, use 1/4 cup of mix to 6 ounces boiling water.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Split into 4 layers.
Mix milk, marshmallows and sugar together.
Cook until marshmallows melt. Add vanilla and coconut.
Bring to a boil for one minute.
Cool and spread between layers.
Ice cake as usual.

title: tasty treat
directions: Melt chips.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on baking sheet and chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions on box.
Press this into bottom of baking dish.
Combine
the
soup, chicken, vegetables, salt and pepper, then pour
this over the stuffing crust.
Place the biscuits on a floured
surface
and roll out enough
to	cover the top of the baking
dish.
Bake
at
400° until biscuits brown.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Combine the pineapple (with liquid) and vanilla pudding mix in a deep bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup of coconut, 1/4 cup of walnuts and all cherries.
Mix and sprinkle top with remaining coconut and walnuts.
Garnish with cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 1 stick oleo and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and pack in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Combine cold margarine, eggs, powdered sugar, vanilla and 1 teaspoon butter flavoring and beat 8 to 10 minutes at high speed.
Spread over crust and chill.

title: gulliver creme corn
directions: Heat corn, milk, cream and seasoning to a rolling boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Blend butter and flour.
Pour into mixture.
Remove from heat.
Can sprinkle cheese on top, if desired.

title: baked cranberry sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: bread and butter pickles(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumber is crisp-tender and onion is transparent.
Ladle into glass jar (rinsed with hot water to prevent cracking).
Cover.
Cool slightly and refrigerate.

title: roasted potatoes with garlic and rosemary(makes about 3 cups)
directions: Preheat oven to 450° with rack in lower third.
Bring 6 quarts salted water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Heat oil, garlic and rosemary on a large baking sheet (with sides) on stove top over medium-low heat.
Do not allow garlic to brown.
To heat oil, place the pan directly on the stove top.

title: braised soy sauce chicken
directions: In a pan large enough to hold all chicken, bring to a boil the water, soy sauce, wine, ginger root and sesame seed oil, then add chicken.
Sauce should reach 1/2 up side of chicken.
Reduce heat to moderate and cook 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and stir in sugar.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Turn off and let sit for 2 to 3 hours.

title: ozark honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Nuts, raisins or coconut may be added to mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: oven cheese fondue
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Remove crust from bread.
Cut bread into cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings with mixer.
Then pour mixture over bread cubes, cheese and onion.
Pour into ungreased baking dish and bake uncovered 1 hour or until center is set.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix soups and Burgundy in large boiler or crock-pot.
Add beef cubes and cook at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder to flour.
Add flour, sour cream and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.
Mix well.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In a cup, put 1 teaspoon sugar, 1 package yeast and 3/4 cup warm water.
Set aside.
In a bowl, put 2 tablespoons shortening, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 cup sugar, and pour in 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and beaten egg. Add enough flour (5 to 6 cups) to make soft dough.
Place in refrigerator until ready to make into rolls.
Let rolls stand 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook bacon.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except salt.
Cover and cook in large pot until fish flakes easily.
Salt to taste.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Then combine the noodles with other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust; chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit or garnished with sliced strawberries.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: twice cooked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes 1 hour at 450°, uncovered. Saute onion and red pepper in margarine until onion is transparent. Scoop insides out and mix with the onion and red pepper. Add cheese and enough milk to make potatoes fluffy. Mound into potato shells and bake at 350° until heated throughout and until they are bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken (strips or pieces).
Heat soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with poppy seed.
Pour melted butter on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This recipe will make two casserole dishes (one 9 x 13-inch and one smaller).
If you make two, you can freeze one.
Just don't put the cracker crumb mix and butter until you want to cook it.

title: stately coconut layer cake
directions: Cream
shortening;
gradually
add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Combine
flour,
baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix
well
after each addition.
Stir in flavorings. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick comes out	clean. Cool
in
pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans
and
let
cool completely.
Spread Lemon-Orange Filling between layers.
Spread top
and
sides
with
Luscious White Frosting and sprinkle with coconut.
Yield: one 3-layer cake.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Mix 1/2 pineapple juice and cornstarch to make a smooth paste.
Add the rest of juice, pineapple and drained beets.
Cook on medium heat; stir often to keep from sticking or lumping.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients into a soft spread.
Use with vegetables or crackers.

title: parmesan topped asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blanche asparagus in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Arrange spears in a shallow ovenproof serving dish.
Pour melted butter over asparagus.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cold german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes thinly.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, dry mustard, sugar and pepper into dressing.
Pour over potatoes, celery, onion and pimiento; mix.
Top with crumbled bacon and parsley; chill well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until done. Peel and use electric mixer to smash and smooth. Mix ingredients in order given. Pour into pastry shells. Bake in hot oven (425°) 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to moderate (350°) and continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pork chops and rice in a pot
directions: Use a crock-pot for this recipe.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 of strawberries; dissolve cornstarch in lemon juice and add to strawberries.
Add sugar and cook in skillet until thickened and transparent.
Slice rest of berries and fold into cooked mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: spinach pie
directions: Clean and chop spinach and scallions. Place in large mixing bowl. Add Feta cheese, cottage cheese and seasoning. Add mixed eggs and mix ingredients well. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Place 8 pastry sheets into pan. Brush each pastry sheet with melted butter. Spread spinach mixture evenly and cover with 8 more pastry sheets, brushing each with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown. Serve hot or cold.

title: jerry's old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes with Miracle Whip.
Add eggs, dill, relish, celery, pepper and mustard.
Refrigerate before and after serving.

title: indian bars(brownies)
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar and eggs; mix thoroughly. Sift flour with baking powder.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check after 20 minutes.
Do not overcook!
Should be slightly gooey in the middle.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl; pour over cucumbers.
Let sit 4 hours and then drain.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together. Roll into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with fork. Bake at 350° until done.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocado; remove flesh from pit.
Place in bowl with lemon or lime juice; mash with fork.
Stir in onion, chilies, tomato, garlic and salt, if desired.
Cover; chill.
Yield: About 1 1/2 cups.

title: pork chops and wild rice
directions: Brown pork chops in hot oil.
Pour off excess grease. Add rice.
Place a slice of tomato, bell pepper and onion on each chop. Salt and pepper to taste. Add approximately 2 cups water. Bring to a boil.
Cut down to simmer. Cook about 40 minutes.
May need to add water from time to time.
Can hold on the stove for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tempura
directions: Slice vegetables to desired thickness or leave whole or into bite
size chunks.
For vegetables, can use string beans, onion, cauliflower,
broccoli,
eggplant
or asparagus or try something new.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and put into two well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Brush tops with margarine.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: savory chicken soup
directions: In a stock pot, combine broth, seasonings, vegetables, chicken and rice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender.
Add a little cold water to cornstarch and stir into soup to thicken.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Taste for seasoning and add a dash of cayenne pepper, if desired.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Heat butter in saucepan and add onion, cooking until onion is wilted.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Add the milk, stirring rapidly with a wire whisk. Add spinach to sauce.
Pour into blender container.
Blend a few seconds.
Add cayenne, garlic powder and nutmeg.
Transfer back to pan, reheating until mixture just comes to a boil.
May be chilled and served cold with a teaspoon of whipped cream on top.
When I serve it hot, we enjoy grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oats, boiling water, butter, salt, molasses and honey. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine oat mixture and yeast. Add flour slowly.
Mix.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until double in size.
Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Let rise to top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mary webber chocolate pie
directions: Combine milk, eggs and dry ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 15 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
(Double boiler method:
cook until very thick.)
After pie has cooled, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: corn puffs
directions: Combine eggs and corn in bowl.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, paprika and pepper. Fold this into corn mixture. Drop by small spoonfuls into fat heated to 365°.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: neapolitan ice cream sandwich cake
directions: Remove cake from foil pan; line pan with plastic wrap.
With serrated knife, slice cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place bottom cake layer back into prepared pan and place in freezer.
In small bowl, stir together 1 cup ice cream and strawberry syrup; spread over cake layer in pan.
Gently place second cake layer on top of strawberry mixture; immediately return to freezer.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni according to directions on package. Add milk and butter to beaten eggs. Add salt.
Place alternating layers of shredded cheese and macaroni in buttered baking dish. Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Stir together and cook slowly for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, oil, eggs and 1 cup of juice from strawberries.
(If strawberries do not have 1 cup juice, finish with water.)
Bake at 350° until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad dressing; mix well, then add salad dressing and mix again.

title: apricot bars
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Stir in oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of crumbs into an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: borscht in a minit
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Top with sour cream to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, soup, carrots and milk.
Stir until creamy.
Melt butter in pan and add seasoning packet from stuffing mix.
Simmer about 10 minutes and add croutons.
Sprinkle croutons on bottom of pan. Add squash and onion to creamy mixture.
Pour in pan on croutons. Sprinkle some croutons on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: *Onion, celery, broccoli, carrots, green peppers, radishes, zucchini, squash, cauliflower, cucumber or tomatoes; may use canned tomatoes.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Brown sausage in skillet; drain off fat.
Add peppers, cheese, onions, pimentos, milk and soup.
Mix well.
Add noodles and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon, nutmeg and food coloring; bring to boil.
Add butter and cool.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; cut into 6-inch squares.
Place apples in each square. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; dot with butter.
Fold corners to center.

title: chicken honolulu
directions: Cut chicken into chunks. Coat with flour and brown.
Combine preserves, barbecue sauce, onion and soy sauce; pour over drained browned chicken. Cover and simmer 40 minutes. Add chestnuts the last 10 minutes. Serve chicken on a bed of hot rice.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cheese.
Pour half the mixture into a greased hot skillet.
Sprinkle half the cheese over that.
Repeat with remainder of batter and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: moms cheese ball
directions: Mix together in large bowl, Cover and place in fridge to firm. Divide in 2. Shape into 2 balls on wax paper. Roll in chopped pecans and top with
a cherry.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breast.
(I simmer mine in water with onion, celery, carrot, bay leaf, pepper corns, salt, etc.)
Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese and seasoning.
Drain broccoli and arrange in bottom of flat, greased casserole (3 qt.).
Sprinkle generously with parmesan cheese. Remove skin from chicken and take chicken from bone, pulling apart in pieces, and spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle again with parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with parmesan and paprika. Dot with butter.
Cook 30 to 40 min. in 305° oven or until bubbly and hot through.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: iron skillet pound cake(1940 recipe)
directions: Cream Crisco, vanilla and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Continue creaming and add slowly well beaten egg yolk. Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately, beating in dry ingredients and stirring in milk.
First and last addition should be flour.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold in.
Pour batter into iron frying pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix salt with cucumbers and onions.
Let stand 2 hours.
Rinse the cucumbers with cold water and drain.
Mix sugar and vinegar with cucumbers and onions until sugar is dissolved; add celery seed.
Place in plastic bags with liquid and seal.
Freeze.

title: tangy deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mix with mayonnaise, mustard and horseradish.
Fill each half; sprinkle on a little paprika.

title: shrimp, feta and tomato salad
directions: In large heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of oil over moderate heat.
Saute shrimp for 2 minutes; stir until firm. Transfer to large bowl; let cool.
In small bowl, whisk the lemon juice, vinegar, zest, oregano, salt and pepper.
Whisk 4 tablespoons of oil.
Toss shrimp, Feta, tomatoes and olives. Chill.
Serves 4.

title: pickled deer heart
directions: Simmer heat for 30 minutes.
Remove fat and cube heart into 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil for 2 hours.
Heat pickling solution for 5 minutes (medium heat).
Drain meat and add to pickling solution and refrigerate.
Ready after 24 hours.

title: soft granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix brown sugar, oil and eggs in a large bowl with spoon until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except Honey Glaze. Spread mixture in pan with spatula, patting evenly with hand. Bake just until center is set, but not firm, 17 to 22 minutes; cool 15 minutes.
Drizzle evenly with Honey Glaze.
Bars can be stored, tightly covered, for up to 2 weeks, or wrap bars tightly in moisture-proof wrap and freeze up to 6 months.
Makes 40 bars.

title: sauerkraut and noodle casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Brown pork and cut in cubes.
Partially cook noodles.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish and top with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Put on about 10 p.m. and cook all night.

title: double boiler 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar and water in top of double boiler.
Beat on high speed 1 minute with electric mixer. Place over boiling water (water should not touch bottom of pan); beat on high speed 7 minutes.
Remove pan from boiling water.
Add vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes longer on high speed.

title: aunt ann's rolls
directions: Heat water until hot enough to melt butter.
Add sugar and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, let set for 5 minutes or until yeast is bubbly.
Add egg and salt.
Add flour 1 cup at a time and mix well. When you have a soft dough, turn out on a floured surface and knead well.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Pinch or cut into rolls and place on a greased pan.
Cover and let rise again until double in bulk.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat through.
Serve on buns.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Use double boiler.
Place chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Do not boil.
Blend in peanut butter.
Pour in peanuts. Stir until peanuts are covered.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper on cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: south of the border chicken breasts
directions: Pound breasts to flatten.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter. Add chicken and saute about 2 minutes on each side.

title: potatoes elegante(sour cream and cheese potatoes)
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except for potatoes.
Add to potatoes.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered, in 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
While baking, stir a few times for even cooking.

title: tony's pork steak and potatoes
directions: Slice butter in a 9 x 13 pan.
Slice potatoes, not peeled, to cover the bottom of pan.
Salt and pepper.
Lay pork chops (steaks) over potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Place in preheated oven at 400 degrees.
Bake until done.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Make into small balls.
Place in pressure saucepan in which the tomato soup and water are heating.
Cook 10 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.
Let cool by itself.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: crab won ton
directions: Mix crab, chopped scallions, Tabasco sauce and cream cheese. Put 1 to 2 teaspoons filling in each won ton wrapper and fold/crimp to enclose filling.
Deep fry until golden brown. Drain and serve with your choice of hot or mild sauces.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add cherry juice.
Drain pineapple and mix with marshmallows.
Whip the cream and fold in fruit.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate.
The flavor improves after it cools several hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and place in casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter.
Put crushed corn flakes on top, then pour butter over corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: impossible hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in frying pan.
Drain.
Spread in bottom of large pie pan or square pan.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and Bisquick together.
Pour over hamburger.
Top with cheese (grated).
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and brown (5 to 8 minutes).

title: orange butter sauce
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add corn syrup gradually.	Stir in orange peel.
Delicious when served warm. Good with bake Hen,
roasted Duck.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 3 3/4 cups mix, about 15 (6-ounce) servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Pour in Eagle Brand; mix. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Makes a lot.

title: grandma's mincemeat
directions: Boil meat and cool in liquor.
Mix all together and simmer slowly for one hour.

title: carrot tea bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil in large mixing bowl.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and add to egg mixture.
Stir in carrots.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until center springs back.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or a cream cheese frosting.

title: southwest salsa dressing
directions: In small bowl, stir all ingredients together.
Makes 4 servings (2 tablespoons per serving).

title: pecan chicken
directions: Combine honey and mustard. Spread on both sides of chicken. Dredge chicken in chopped pecans. Place in lightly greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: molasses donuts
directions: Mix ingredients and blend well.
Roll, cut with donut cutter and fry as other donuts.
Yields 30 to 36 donuts.

title: cinnamon puffins
directions: In a mixing bowl; combine flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
In another bowl beat shortening, 1/2 cup sugar, egg and vanilla until well blended.
Add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture and beat in the milk until smooth.
Lighlty grease muffin pan and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar, then egg, then flour sifted with salt and soda.
To this add melted butter.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Mix together and cook for 30 minutes.
If chili is thin, decrease water.
If too thick, add more water.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Crush enough strawberries to make 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in the water and crushed berries. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Cool.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown onion in fat in large frying pan, then add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Next, pour half of sauce on chicken and bake, uncovered, at 500° for 30 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: pedro special
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain grease.
Stir tomato sauce, oregano and chili powder into meat.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all together and cook in crock pot 4-6 hours.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Measure and mix dry ingredients (except cocoa) into a large mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Mix water, butter and cocoa in saucepan; melt, but do not boil.
Add to batter; blend well.
Pour into a 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and ice.
Very moist.

title: tirami-su
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar together.
Add Mascarpone cheese; blend well.
Beat egg whites until peaks form; fold into cheese mixture.

title: like orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: cinnamon nut crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cover large baking sheet
with parchment paper or aluminum foil.
Combine brown sugar, walnuts, butter and cinnamon in a small bowl.

title: fresh coconut icing
directions: Boil sugar, water and cream of tartar to soft ball stage (can be picked up when tested in cold water).
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar syrup to egg whites and beat until thick.
Add vanilla. Frost cake then sprinkle with coconut.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour. Roll balls the size of a small walnut and flatten with glass or fork.
Sprinkle with sugar or seed.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.
(Color with food coloring for Christmas.)

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in a tightly covered glass jar.
To serve:
Place 3 to 4 teaspoons of the mix in 1 cup boiling water.
Experiment with quantity to suit taste.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; beat eggs slightly.
Add butter, salt and sugar mixture, syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven and bake for 10 minutes at 375° and 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: easy microwave ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
Pour over cheese and cook for 30 to 35 minutes on high.

title: crisp cheese balls
directions: Soften butter to mix with cheeses, salt and pepper.
Add flour and mustard.
Mix in Rice Krispies by hand and roll into small balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
These freeze well.
Makes over 100.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Blend flour and butter as for crust; stir in pecans.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and cream cheese; spread on crust.
Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Pour over top.
Chill to set. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: baked stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peppers.
Cut tops of peppers; remove seeds and veins.
Put in a pan; cover with water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from water and stuff with hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake, following instructions on box.
Cook pudding and cool or use instant.
In a large punch bowl, start layering cake (cut in slices or chunks), pie filling, pudding and Cool Whip. Start with cake; end with Cool Whip.

title: almond bean casserole
directions: Combine beans with soup.
Place in shallow baking dish. Arrange small onions around edge of casserole and sprinkle with buttered crumbs and toasted almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yum yum cheese cake
directions: Use oblong cake pan.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in pan. Grease pan good with margarine.
Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and melted margarine.
Mix with a fork, then pat in pan.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When removed from oven and still hot, spread 1 jar marshmallow cream on top and cool.
When cooled, frost with the following chocolate frosting.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar to crushed pretzels.
Mix well. Add margarine.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry sorbet
directions: Heat water and sugar in large saucepan over medium heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer gently until sugar is completely dissolved.
Cool.
Press raspberries through wire mesh sieve over medium bowl to remove seeds (yields about 2 cups juice).
Combine juice, sugar, syrup, raspberries, Schnapps and lemon juice in large bowl.

title: layer surprise pie
directions: Mix butter, flour
and nuts and press in pie pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake	at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Put on top of cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Spread all of the onion, celery and carrots on the bottom of a large Dutch oven.
Rub roast with garlic and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place roast on top of vegetables in center of pan and add water until pan is 3/4 filled. Roast, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Turn roast and cook another 2 hours, or until the internal temperature is 170°

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring to a boil: vinegar, sugar, salt, celery and mustard seed until sugar is dissolved.
Pour, while hot, over onions and cuke slices.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Cukes will settle and a few more slices can be added.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add oil and beat until creamy.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and allspice.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to bowl. Cool slightly.
Combine dressing, soy sauce and sugar.
Stir into warm rice.
Cover and chill.
Fold the remaining ingredients before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: curriet fruit
directions: Combine margarine,
sugar and curry powder.
Bring to a boil. Drain
the	fruit.	Arrange in a shallow 2 quart baking dish (about 10
x
x	1
1/2-inch).
Pour sauce over it and garnish with cherries.
Bake at 325° until bubbly (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Put crackers in bowl.
Mix in separate bowl the other ingredients.
Pour over crackers; stir often during the day. Store in airtight container.

title: carrot soup
directions: Cook the carrots and onion together in boiling water until tender; drain.
Puree in blender; empty into pot with broth, butter, sugar and rice.
Bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add half and half and stir until heated through. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: cake decorator icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat at low to medium speed at least 10 minutes.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix 1/2 cup oleo with corn flakes for topping.
Mix wet ingredients; add to potatoes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: good chocolate pie
directions: Place the sliced bananas in the bottom of the pie crust. Beat together the remaining ingredients and pour into crust. Chill in refrigerator until set.
Top with fat free Cool Whip.

title: cranberry crimson mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually whisk salad dressing into gelatin until smooth.
Stir in cranberry-orange sauce and applesauce.
Pour into 5-cup ring, which has been sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes about 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: raspberry walnut torte
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, confectioners sugar and butter; blend well.
Press mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: hearty chicken and rice soup
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 25 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup butter and corn flakes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and mix with crushed corn flakes.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: In bowl, combine cream cheese, seasoning and garlic powder. Spread on bottom of greased 9-inch pie plate.
Top with pizza sauce and peppers.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with chips.
Makes 3 1/2 cups dip.

title: saucy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes, then uncover and bake 15 minutes. This is best served over rice.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Combine sugars, oil and eggs.
Mix well. Stir in dry ingredients. Add oatmeal, coconut, cornflakes, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop in walnut size pieces on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to oil mixture.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Add grated carrots and nuts.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour, until cake tests done with toothpick.

title: banana carrot bread
directions: Combine bananas, sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer 2 minutes (or 300 strokes by hand).
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold into banana mixture.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Stir into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight before cutting.
May substitute zucchini for carrots.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini in boiling water for 6 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Combine vinaigrette, dill and pepper in bowl.
Stir well. Pour over tortellini.
Toss gently.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cake(no flour)
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased tube pan lined with a brown paper bag.
Bake 2 1/2 hours. After cool, wrap cake in towel and put in container with lid. Sprinkle rum around on top.
Store in a cool place.
Let stand a few weeks before eating.
While storing, keep slightly moist with rum.

title: award winning chili
directions: Cook tomatoes, green pepper, onion, jalapenos, spices and chorizos until vegetables are tender.

Add vinegar, brown sugar and beans and simmer on low for 1-2 hours or cook in a slow cooker (low heat) for 5-6 hours. chorizos: Brown sausage in a frying pan before adding to the chili, but you can buy chorizos (beef, pork, or chicken) in natural casings that are really good too.

title: seven-layer mexican dip
directions: Combine sour cream and seasoning. Mix well. Spread bean dip on bottom of a 12 inch round glass serving bowl. Top with guacamole, sour cream, cheese, scallions, tomatoes and olives.

title: fresh fruit dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine Eagle Brand, sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy; mix in flour, oats and walnuts until thoroughly blended.
On lightly oiled pizza pan or baking sheet, press dough into 12-inch circle, forming rim around edge.
Prick with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Spoon filling evenly onto crust.
Arrange fruit on top of filling.
Garnish with mint leaves, if desired. Chill before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Cook broccoli for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour soup, mayonnaise and cheese over top of broccoli. Put into oven and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: barbecue deer meat
directions: Cook until thick, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve on buns or toast.

title: fritter batter
directions: Add flour, soda and salt to beaten eggs.
Beat in oil.
Stir in milk.
Mix all together.
Add corn, meats or fruits into Fritter Batter.
Drop by level tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry until completely cooked, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Fry at 375°.

title: carolina cornish hens
directions: Cut hens in half lengthwise.
In large skillet, brown hens in butter (or spray pan with Pam or such and save some fat and calories) on all sides.
Remove from skillet and drain off drippings.
Brown sausage in skillet, remove and drain on paper toweling.
Pour drippings from skillet.

title: cereal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl. Stir in cereal.
Beat egg in medium bowl; add milk, oil and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture; mix until moistened.
Mix in raisins.
Spoon in greased muffin pan.
Fill each cup 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix the soup and mayonnaise together.
(Optional - a little lemon juice, a dash of tabasco or garlic.)
Place the chicken in a baking dish.
Next put broccoli over the chicken.
Then spread soup mixture over broccoli.
Top with the cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles and the cheese is melted.

title: butter rings(berlinerkranser)
directions: Mash yolks of hard-boiled eggs very well.
Add raw egg yolks, blending to a smooth paste.
Cream butter and vanilla, gradually adding sugar and creaming until fluffy after each addition.
Add egg mixture in thirds, blending well after each addition.
Add sifted flour in fourths, again blending well each time.
Wrap dough in foil and chill thoroughly.
With hands, roll small pieces of dough to pencil thickness, about 4 to 4 1/2-inches long. Paint ends with egg white and overlap to form a wreath.
Brush egg white on top of each cookie and sprinkle with perle sugar or crushed sugar cubes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen.
Store in cool place.
Freeze well.

title: upside-down pancakes
directions: *Try fresh apple, frozen blueberries or canned peaches.

title: shrimp and crab salad
directions: Mix bread cubes, onion, eggs and celery.
About 4 or 5 hours before serving, add shrimp, crab and dressing.
Toss well and serve.

title: beef-corn dandy
directions: Brown meat with onions and pepper.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Turn off heat and add cheese. Let stand until cheese melts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Slice mushrooms and brown in butter. Beat eggs and pour over mushrooms. Cook until almost done and add sausage to mixture. Top with cheese. Place in oven until cheese is melted. Warm tortillas and serve with picante sauce.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Take biscuits and press into muffin cups, bringing dough to top edge of cups.
Spoon mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: arizona mountain soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Cover with 3 cups of water. Let stand overnight. Do not drain.
Simmer covered for 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Drain, reserving 2 cups of liquid.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Drop the chicken livers into just enough boiling water to cover them.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes; drain well.
Put the livers through the finest blade of a food chopper.
Add onion, margarine, cayenne, salt, nutmeg, dry mustard and cloves and blend well.
Pack in a crock or small glass jar.
Store in the refrigerator for at least 12 hours.
The pate will keep for about 1 week.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: flour frosting
directions: Put flour and milk in saucepan.
Thicken.
Run beater in saucepan until creamy.
Cool.
Put shortening, margarine, vanilla, cocoa and sugar in bowl.
Beat.
Combine flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Flour, salt and pepper chicken.
Brown in frying pan.
Remove from the pan.
Add the onions, which have been sliced.
Brown slightly; drain.
Return chicken to the pan.
Add the tomatoes; mash tomatoes.
Add the water, celery, salt and pepper and poultry seasoning.
Cover and simmer.
Remove chicken.
Cut into pieces and return to pan.
Add corn and lima beans.
Add to stew and cook 20 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in two layers.
When cool, split to make four layers.
Mix sour cream, coconut and sugar.
Reserve 1 cup of coconut mixture and spread remaining between cake layers.
Mix Cool Whip and reserved coconut mixture and frost top and sides of cake. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Debone and cut into small pieces.
Put into bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix chicken broth, Veg-All, celery soup and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour and milk very well.
Melt margarine and mix with flour and milk.
Mix well.
Spoon over the chicken mixture.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 1 hour and until brown on top.

title: favorite raisin cake
directions: Place water and raisins in a saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and boil for ten minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool completely.

title: tangy cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar, onion and green pepper.
Stir in black pepper and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in diced tomato and cucumber.
Pour in 1 quart mold, which has been well-greased.
Chill until firm. Unmold on lettuce leaves.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Discard seed from peppers.
Put peppers and onions through food chopper.
Add salt; cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes and drain off liquid and
discard.
Bring sugar and vinegar to boil; add pepper mixture and simmer for 20 minutes. Ladle into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Process at 212° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Separate Wheaties and butter into two portions.
Reserve 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese also.
Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, garlic powder, 1/2 of Wheaties and butter.
Pour into casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 Wheaties and 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: one-dish bistro stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, blend savory herb with garlic recipe soup mix with water.
Bring to a boil, then continue boiling, stirring occasionally, 1 minute or until slightly thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables to skillet.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, five minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over hot rice. Garnish, if desired, with chopped fresh parsley.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in applesauce. Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: In a large dish, mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix. Pour taco sauce over, then lettuce, then tomatoes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into 3 balls.
Cover with pecans and refrigerate.

title: mexican cheese puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix, margarine, chilies and egg in medium bowl.
Stir in cheese.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 1-inch apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix.
Chill and serve with potato chips, crackers, celery sticks, cauliflowerets or radish roses.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: onion souffle squares
directions: In a food processor, mince garlic.
Finely chop half of the onions.
Remove.
Chop remaining onions.
Remove.

title: apple pie(quickie)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and nutmeg together.
Mix with apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cut several pats of butter or margarine and place on top of apples.
(Do not use butter or margarine if you freeze pie; use it when you remove from freezer and cook.) Can go straight from freezer to oven.
Cook in preheated oven at 300° until done, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
If frozen, 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from bones.
Put back in pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Let come to boil again.
Add cut up cheese; stir until melted.
Add milk slowly; heat to almost boiling.
Very good on cold days and for colds and flu.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and microwave 17 to 21 minutes on High. Stir, cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: fruit kabobs with dip
directions: Alternate any 3 pieces of fruit on plastic or wooden toothpicks.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve the jello
in boiling water. Add orange sherbet and set until partially firm. Add oranges, pineapple and bananas. Fold in whipped cream. Put into mold and allow to set.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook the zucchini in salted water in saucepan for 2 minutes; drain. Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Layer dry mixture and zucchini in pastry lined pie plate until all ingredients are used. Dot with butter.
Top with remaining pastry. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until browned.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine yeast, water, 1 cup sugar and 2 cups flour.
In another bowl, scald milk, then add Crisco, salt, eggs and 1 cup sugar. When cooled to lukewarm, add yeast mixture.
Add approximately 12 cups flour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bonnie's corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken breasts and cut in bite size pieces.
Cover glass bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with chicken.
Cover chicken with Swiss cheese slices.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 1/2 can milk. Pour over chicken and cheese.
Melt stick of margarine and mix with Stove Top stuffing (with seasoning) and put on top.
Cover with foil and let set 2 hours.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° with foil left on.

title: bass's green eggplant supreme
directions: Cut green eggplants (sometimes called white) into small pieces. Finely chop other ingredients.
Place 3/4-inch of water in saucepan with seasonings.
Bring to hard boil.
With heat on high, continue to boil.
Add other items, cover and occasionally.
When tender, remove lid and continue to boil all liquid out.
Stir frequently. Add margarine when melted.
Remove from burner.
Cover until ready to serve.

title: quick mexican dish
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasonings and corn.
At this point, I'll add all of my spices (oregano, sweet basil, salsa, hot red peppers, etc.).
Add soups and tomatoes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add pepper.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Stir now and then.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fudgy oatmeal squares
directions: Stir the oats and boiling water together, then set aside.
In large bowl, mix white sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add the oat mixture, shortening and vanilla and beat well again. Add eggs.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar or your favorite frosting.

title: harriet's orange jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Add oranges and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 2 to 3 hours until set.

title: hazelnut pumpkin bread
directions: Blend together	sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin; mix well. Sift together
dry
ingredients and add alternately with water to pumpkin mixture.
Stir
in nuts and raisins.
Divide batter among 3 greased 5
x
9-inch
loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: 1917 war cake
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook 3 minutes after reaching boiling point.
Add Crisco.
When cooled, add soda dissolved in a little water.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: cranberry fruit relish
directions: Put through food chopper.
The fruit should be cut in quarters and the seeds removed before chopping, but the peeling is left on. Add to the chopped fruit 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Blend thoroughly and let stand for a few hours before serving.
This amount makes 1 1/2 quarts of relish or enough for 50 servings or 2 tablespoons each. This will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat until smooth. Add rolled oats, vanilla, nuts and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoonful two inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into prepared graham cracker crust.

title: violet's chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into an 8-inch square pan.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
In the first one, add the vanilla.
In the second, add the vinegar.
In the third, add the cooking oil.
Add 1 cup of water to the whole mixture.
Stir with a fork until blended and bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set oven at 350°.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Beat until light and fluffy.

title: tea cakes or granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup sugar.
Blend in 1 egg.
Sift together and add to mixture, salt, baking powder and sifted flour.
Blend vanilla into mixture.
Roll into balls and pat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: upper crust chicken or turkey
directions: Trim crust from bread; remove crusts.
Cut bread diagonally into quarters.
Set aside.
Cut crusts into cubes in a large bowl with seasoning, celery and 1 3/4 cups of the cheese; toss together.

title: puppy chow
directions: In very large bowl, combine cereal, raisins and nuts.
Melt together chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Stir in vanilla and pour over cereal mixture.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook the ground beef and drain.
Cook the green beans.
Mix ground beef, green beans and tomato soup in a casserole dish and spread evenly.
Grate the cheese and sprinkle over first layer. Prepare potatoes and place over cheese; spread evenly.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix pudding with mix according to package directions.
Add Cool Whip.
Starting with pudding, layer in 9 x 13-inch dish with graham crackers.
End with pudding and top with crushed crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: traditional sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine eggs, sweet potatoes, sugar and spices in mixer. Add milk.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean after you put it in center of pie.

title: garbage plates
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and cheese in a cast-iron pan.
Cook until done.
Add soup and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes. Smother with cheese and place under broiler for 5 minutes.

title: mexi-taco sandwiches
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Add the rest.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put on hamburger buns.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; heat until melted.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar.
Add chocolate bits and vanilla.
Arrange by teaspoonful on wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Place cookies in a 350° oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven 6 hours or overnight. Makes about 30 to 60 cookies.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out thin on a floured surface.
Cut into strips; then pinch off in small pieces.
Drop dough into deboned cooked chicken and broth that is boiling.
Cover.
Boil 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In saucepan, brown the ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add the tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour. Cook the noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Combine the egg, cottage cheese and 1 teaspoon of salt; mix well. Grease a 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 the noodles, 1/2 the meat sauce, 1/2 the cottage cheese, 1/2 the Mozzarella and 1/2 the Parmesan.
Repeat layers.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: maple nut torte
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Remove from pan. Slice off top of cake so top is flat.
Split cake to make 2 layers.
(To split, mark side of cake with toothpicks and cut with long, serrated knife.)
Place bottom layer on serving plate.
Stir cinnamon, nutmeg, maple flavoring and pecans into whipped topping. Spread 1 1/2 cups of topping mixture over bottom layer.
Place other layer on top.
Frost top and side of cake with remaining topping mixture.
Garnish with pecan halves, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: south of the border wraps
directions: In a bowl, mash beans slightly. Add salsa, onions and cilantro. Spread over tortillas. Sprinkle with tomato and cheese. Roll up tightly. Melt butter in a large skillet. Add tortillas, seam side down. Cook until golden on all sides, adding additional butter as needed. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: wonder salad
directions: Chop the broccoli, green pepper, celery, cauliflower and cabbage. Combine the sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar, oil, poppy seed and chopped onion.
Marinate dressing 6 hours or overnight.

title: texas yum yum cake
directions: Mix softened butter, flour and 1 cup nuts.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese (softened), powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Then prepare vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on box. Spread vanilla pudding on cream cheese layer.
Then add chocolate pudding.
Then top with Cool Whip and then nuts.

title: *hot mulled cider
directions: Mix cider, salt, sugar and lemon juice.
Place spices in a small cheesecloth bag.
Place in cider and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla. Reserve 1/2 cup batter for icing.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in lightly greased and floured tube pan.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine olive oil with lemon juice.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and basil to make marinade.
Chop onion.
Combine chicken and marinade with onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and turn once during cooking.

title: colonial innkeeper's pie
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Add 2/3 cup sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/4 cup butter or margarine and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Set sauce aside.
Mix and stir flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add margarine, vanilla and milk. Beat 2 minutes.
Add 1 egg and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour sauce over batter and sprinkle top with 1/2 cup pecans or walnuts.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°. Serve with whipped cream.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and eggs.
Add bread and melted butter.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: hollowed rye bread
directions: Combine soup mix, mayonnaise, sour cream, chestnuts and spinach.
Place dip in hollowed out rye loaf.
Serve dip with bread pieces from the hollow, then rip off pieces until the loaf is gone.
Makes about 2 cups of dip.

title: congealed ambrosia
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 cup boiling water in a bowl. Chill until partially set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: raisin cranberry pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil and cook until cranberries pop.
Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and vanilla.
Bake at 425° for 1/2 hour or until brown.
This is a 2 crust pie.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Add carrots and mix well.
Refrigerate several days.

title: red kidney beans
directions: Cook beans in a large pot, covered; cook on low.
Add ham or other seasoning meat to beans.
In meat drippings, saut onions, garlic, celery, parsley and bay leaves; add to beans and cook for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Add water if necessary while cooking.
Cook until done. Serve over rice and serve.

title: chocolate mousse(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients on medium speed.
Freeze and serve.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple chunks on bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix flour and sugar; sprinkle on top of pineapple.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Melt margarine and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon dip
directions: Blend ingredients together at medium speed until smooth.
Pour mixture into small bowl.
Stir in capers.
Cover bowl and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on cracker or use as dip for chips.

title: curry chicken divine
directions: Bake the chicken.
Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain. Put broccoli in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken. Sprinkle mixture with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add Ragu and seasonings.
Set aside.
In a bowl, lightly beat the egg.
Add cottage cheese, salt and pepper. In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1/3 of the meat sauce.
Cover this with 1/3 of the cottage cheese mixture.
Place uncooked noodles on top of cottage cheese, then sprinkle 1/2 of both cheeses.
Second layer is 1/3 meat sauce and 1/3 cottage cheese followed by another layer of noodles and the remaining two cheeses.
The last layer consists of noodles, followed by the rest of the meat sauce and the rest of the cottage cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Mix brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and hot peppers in a pot.
Cook until mixtures comes to a boil.
Mix flour and water together as if making gravy.
Add to pepper mixture; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour in hot jars and seal with hot lids and rings.

title: deluxe chocolate layer cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. Combine chocolate, milk and butter in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl until thickened, using electric mixer at high speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is very thick and lemon colored.
Beat in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream to egg mixture, beating well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate mixture, beating at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour batter into 3 greased and waxed paper-lined 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool in pans on racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on racks.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In saucepan, combine peaches, water and 1/2 cup of sugar. Bring to a boil.
Keep hot.
Beat egg, 1/2 cup of sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add milk.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread batter in greased baking dish.
Pour hot peaches over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Serve with cream.
Serves 6.

title: peppers in oil
directions: You will also need clean canning jars and new canning jar lids.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat pot; add butter to melt.
Add onions, peppers, celery and garlic and cook until translucent.
Add tomato sauce, seasonings and 2 cups water.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes.
Serve alone or over rice.

title: toffee
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil. Layer pan with crackers (5 across by 7 down).
Melt butter, then add brown sugar.
Stir thoroughly and pour over crackers.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour bag of semi-sweet chocolate on top.
Let melt, then spread.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate and cool 1/2 hour.
Remove foil; break into pieces.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended; chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: winter carnival casserole
directions: Heat corn oil.
Add finely chopped onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add ground beef; brown stirring often.
Pour and save 1/4 cup liquid from canned tomatoes.
Add remaining tomatoes, Karo syrup, salt, chili powder, pepper and bay leaf to meat mixture.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 1/4 cup tomato liquid; stir into meat mixture. Bring to boil, stirring.
Add 3 cups cooked macaroni or rice; pour into 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: wine drop cookies
directions: Nutmeats and raisins may be added or you may use both.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Mix lemonade with cold water as directed on can and chill until very cold.
Spoon 1 or 2 scoops raspberry sherbet into tall glasses.
Pour lemonade over top.
Top with a spoonful of whipped topping and a cherry.

title: chicken breast with garlic, herbs and cheese
directions: Blend together butter, garlic cloves, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Dip both sides of chicken in butter mixture.
Dip one side of chicken into bread crumb mixture.
Place breaded side down in shallow casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Top with another piece of chicken dipped and greased as before, breaded side up.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white chip brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl until foamy; gradually beat in sugar.
Add butter and vanilla; beat until blended.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in white chips.
Spread batter into prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix in flour to make a smooth dough.
Pinch off balls 1 1/2-inch in diameter. Form into crescents.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 50.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix chicken, celery, 1/2 of the cheese, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and seasoning. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Cover with tomato slices. Bake 35 minutes and top with remaining cheese and potato chips. Continue baking until cheese melts.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: fluffy divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until they form standing peaks.
Boil sugar, Karo and water until it spins a thread or 250° on candy thermometer.
Pour this mixture slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Let cool somewhat, then drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hamburger mcbake
directions: In saucepan, combine hamburger, soup and water.
Simmer, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn and uncooked macaroni.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes.
Toss together crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes more.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Dip each pork chop into salad dressing, then into bread crumbs. Place in a glass dish; cover with wax paper.
Microwave at 50% for 15 minutes.
Turn chops over and microwave at 50% for an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: green salad
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over jello; let cool to lukewarm and put in cream cheese.
Mix together.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Put in refrigerator and let cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add vinegar while beating (do not overbeat); fold in raisins, pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine orange juice and next 4 ingredients in a bowl. Mix the two bowls together; stir until moist. Fold in berries. Divide batter into muffin cups lined with paper or sprayed with oil. Sprinkle tops with extra tablespoon of sugar, if desired. Bake at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of pastry shell.
Pour filling over bananas. Cover; chill 4 hours, or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream; garnish with remaining banana slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook 1 package Uncle Ben's wild rice according to directions. Add to the mixture of the first 5 ingredients and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: caesar croutons
directions: Prepare garlic olive oil one to several days in advance.
Slice 6 cloves of garlic lengthwise in quarters; let stand in 1 cup olive oil (or you may use salad oil or half of each).

Cut each slice of bread in 5 strips one way, then across 5 times to make squares. Cut enough bread to spread out on cookie sheet; pour a little garlic olive oil over the bread squares on cookie sheet.
Heat in extremely slow oven (225°) for 2 hours.
Croutons should be very dry.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Store in jar in refrigerator. Serve on salads or vegetables.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots about 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine carrots with onion and pepper in large bowl.
