Pour in remaining ingredients. Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 5 cups.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat salad oil in skillet; add rice and fry until slightly brown.
Add onion; fry until soft, then add meat, soy sauce, chicken stock, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until rice is done, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove, cover and let rice dry out about 5 minutes.
Push rice to side of skillet.
Scramble eggs until they are semi-solid, then mix into rice.
Add bean sprouts and cook about 10 minutes.
Rice goes well with Chop Suey recipe.

title: white frosting
directions: Beat together on high speed for 10 minutes.

title: colorful cookie pops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle colored sprinkles on cutting board.
Remove dough from wrapper.
Roll in colored sprinkles to completely cover, pressing sprinkles firmly into dough.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange wooden sticks 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Place dough slices on ends of wooden sticks, extending sticks entire length of dough slices.
If desired, top cookies with additional sprinkles.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute and remove from cookie sheet.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind apricots; add milk and coconut.
Set in refrigerator to chill.
Roll in balls and dust with powdered sugar.

title: arkansas pan fried potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small shoe string size.
Heat oil in an iron skillet on high.
Pour potatoes into skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Turn stove to medium-high; cover and every few minutes turn with a spatula.
Cook until done and brown to your liking.
(Do not stir, they will tear up.)

title: popin' fresh bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients except oats, chocolate chips and coconut.
Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
By hand, stir in the oats and coconut.
Spread dough into pan. Sprinkle dough with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Center will be soft. Cool; cut into bars.

title: lemon parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture.
Coat both sides and place on shallow baking dish.
Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Drizzle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef, toss and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Heat oil, add beef and toss over high heat until cooked to desired doneness.
Add vegetables.
toss until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water. Add to pan, stir and cook until thick.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except flour and soda.
Mix well and then add soda and gradually add flour.
If too sticky to roll, then add more flour.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter, cookie cutters or top of round glass. Bake for 5 to 7 minutes and let cool on rack or put in the freezer before putting icing on them.

title: mama's potato salad
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender; drain and cool.
Peel potatoes; cut into chunks.
Separate egg yolks from whites; set yolks aside.
Chop whites and add to potatoes with onion.
In a small bowl, mash yolks.
Stir in mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Toss well.
Adjust seasonings if necessary.
Spoon into a serving bowl.
Garnish with egg slices and paprika.
Chill before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: favorite punch
directions: Combine Kool-aid and sugar.
Add water and stir to dissolve. Add frozen concentrates.
Chill until serving time.
Pour over ice.
Pour 7-Up slowly down side of bowl.
This makes about 4 quarts.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together and store in an airtight container.
Add 4 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: meatballs with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients except sweet and sour sauce.
Shape into 60 (1-inch) balls.
Place on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Heat sweet and sour sauce in large pot.
Stir in meatballs and serve.

title: fix-it-fast homemade bread
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit salt.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in small amount of fat.
Mix with other ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients about 2 minutes.
Add buttermilk and stir with spoon.
Knead with floured hands, turning over several times until stickiness disappears.
Turn into deep pie plate, 9-inch or deeper if higher loaf is desired.
Cut a cross on top with tip of knife.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes.
Test with knife blade (pushed in).
Knife comes out clean when done.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar if you want it a little sweeter.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Hint:
Fix second sheet of cookies while first is baking.
Sift flour onto waxed paper.
Measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add the soda and salt and sift again.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix raisins, boiling water and soda.
Set overnight.
In the morning, add the flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, sugar and cooking oil. Place in 3 greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans.
(I cut a circle of wax paper to put in the bottom of the can.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with a toothpick.

title: cabbage and potato casserole
directions: Use Pyrex casserole dish.
Shred cabbage, slice potatoes and onion.
Place a layer of cabbage, a layer of onion and a layer of potatoes.
Repeat until bowl is full.
Mix melted butter, mushroom soup, 1/2 cup water and season to taste.
Pour over layered mixture.
Bake in covered bowl until vegetables are tender in a 350° oven.
During baking time, remove lid and stir once.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix syrup and water.
Pour in sugar.
Add pinch of salt.
Boil until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water and threads from spoon (260°).
Pour syrup mixture slowly over beaten egg whites, beating all the while.
Add vanilla, with beater on high speed, beat until mixture is firm.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown sausage, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup
and milk.
Stir and place on fire. Add peanuts.
Cook,
stirring
constantly until a small amount tested in cold
water
forms
a
ball.
Add
butter and vanilla. Beat until mixture	begins to cream.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.

title: cherry spice cake
directions: Mix in order and bake at 350° until done.
Makes 4 layers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place eggs, milk and corn in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add cornmeal; mix well.
Add onion; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and half of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more. Makes 10 servings.

title: trinity burgundy baked trout
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wrap each trout in aluminum foil individually; place in baking pan.
Dot with butter.
Pour the wine over them.
Cover with green peppers, onions and tomato slices.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper or garlic salt and paprika. Seal the aluminum foil.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, or until flesh flakes easily away from the bones when touched with a fork. Serves 1 trout per person.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add ingredients as in the order listed.
It is best to mix all the ingredients by hand, rather than mixer.
This is enough for 2 pies.
Do not preheat oven, then bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.
This recipe was used at the Britling's Cafeteria on 20th Street, downtown Birmingham.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle dry onion soup on bottom of pan, add rice (uncooked). Put browned chicken on top of rice, add celery.
Pour creamed soup (mixed with 1 can water) over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350° covered.

title: antipasto salad tray
directions: Toss together salad ingredients and place on large platter. Then arrange attractively on a bed of lettuce the cheese, summer sausage, artichokes, red peppers, olives, tomatoes and avocados (marinate avocados in lemon juice with slice onion, garlic salt and pepper to taste).
Top with Garlic Romano Vinaigrette.

title: cottage cheese waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Arrange lettuce leaves on plate. Mound salad in center.
Garnish with additional apple slices, if desired.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt the butter in pan.
Put other ingredients in pan, a layer at a time.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix; mix rest of cake mix, oil and 1 egg. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cheese, eggs and sugar (cream well).
Add milk, vanilla and cup of cake mix (it will be runny).
Pour over cake crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Top with grated candy bar.

title: herbed potato bake
directions: Combine margarine, soup mix and rosemary.
Scrub or peel potatoes and cut into slices 1/2 inch thick.
Combine margarine mixture and potatoes; toss gently.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs plus vanilla flavoring.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Mix together all these ingredients.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Make golf ball sized cookies.
Space balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: Stir Jell-O into boiling water, stirring vigorously.
Remove from heat and stir in buttermilk until well blended.
Pour into 5 dessert cups and chill until set.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients; add eggs one at a time, beating until mixture is consistency of whipped cream.
Add vanilla.
Add remaining dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in water. Grease and dust with cocoa a tube pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and drizzle warm frosting over cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream cheese;
add marshmallow cream.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.	Serve with fresh fruit.

title: steak soup
directions: Put butter in soup pot; do not burn.
Add flour and stir to form smooth paste.
Cook over medium heat without burning 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add consomme; stir until smooth and lightly thickened.
Bring to one full boil; add the fresh vegetables, seasoning with the tomatoes to boiling soup, then reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes until vegetables are almost tender.
Add frozen vegetables and browned ground meat.
Simmer additional 15 minutes.
Serve with giant oyster crackers or hot bread.
Serves 8.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Spread graham crackers in a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
Boil sugar and oleo 2 minutes (no more).
Add chopped pecans.
Spread on graham crackers.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 2-crust pie.
Stir together first 5 ingredients. Pour into unbaked crust.
Cut margarine into small pieces and dot top of pie.
Cover with top crust.
Be sure to cut air vents in top crust.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes until crust is brown and juice bubbles through slits in crust.

title: red and white layered salad
directions: Dissolve plain gelatin in cold water.
Add to boiling water. Add rest of ingredients, down to whipped topping.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread in shallow pan.
Allow to set at least 4 hours. Heat V-8 juice to just under boiling.
Add lemon Jell-O and dash of allspice.
Cool; pour over jellied salad and allow to set.
Serves 18.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and quarter apples; put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and cinnamon.
Bring remaining ingredients to a rolling boil. Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: super butterfinger dessert(this is one of my favorite summer desserts.)
directions: Freeze bars ahead of time.
Combine crackers with margarine. Spread 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 of mixture for topping.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream; spread on crust. Spread whipped topping over pudding.
Combine crushed candy bars and reserved crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of whipped topping. Refrigerate for about 4 hours before serving.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and 1 egg.
Beat.
Add another egg.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually with coconut and oatmeal.
Pinch in balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: maw maw's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop on wax paper until set.

title: hanky panky
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage.
Drain and add spices.
Cut cheese into pieces and cook slowly until it melts.
Add a dash of vinegar and sugar.
Serve on party rye bread.
This can be frozen.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Let cool.
Mix gelatin with all other ingredients and pour into mold. Serves 4.

title: creamy chicken with biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat all ingredients in a saucepan. Transfer to baking dish. Top with desired amount of Cheddar cheese. Place refrigerator canned biscuits over top and bake for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and chop apples; set aside.
Pour the oil into a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until the mixture is well blended.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Gradually add flour to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.
Gently fold in chopped apples and pecans.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan and line with wax paper.
Pour in the batter. Bake 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peaches 'n cream delight
directions: Melt margarine in medium size saucepan.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Heat while stirring to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and nuts; press into bottom of ungreased 9-inch pie or square pan.
Spread softened ice cream in crust. Freeze until firm.
Before serving, top with peach or apple filling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham quiche
directions: Combine slightly beaten eggs with cream, cayenne pepper, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Spread ham, cheese and minced onion over bottom of pie crust.
Pour egg-cream mixture over ham and cheese in pie crust.
Place in preheated 400° oven and bake for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300° and continue to bake an additional 30 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, stirring occasionally until browned.
Remove meat; add onion and green pepper.
Saute 2 minutes.
Return meat along with tomato sauce and beef broth.
Simmer round steak 15 to 20 minutes (or sirloin tips 5 to 10 minutes).
Blend together cornstarch, water, soy, sugar and salt.
Add to meat mixture and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta noodles.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Combine the crushed pineapple and sugar.
Heat to a rolling boil, then dissolve jello in the mixture.
Beat the milk until it looks like whipped cream.
Stir the cheese into the pineapple, sugar and jello mixture.
Combine the pineapple mixture with the whipped milk.
Mold in an angel food pan and chill.
Serves 12.

title: elephant ears
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Combine and set aside.
Pinch off piece of bread the size of a small orange; roll out to preferred thickness on floured board.
Have grease in frying pan hot.
Place rolled out dough in hot grease.
Fry 2 minutes on one side; turn and fry 2 minutes on the other side.
Take out of grease and drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with combined sugar and cinnamon. Enjoy.

title: raisin bars
directions: Stir all together.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 350°.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend eggs, soup and mayonnaise.
Add cheese, onion with broccoli.
Mix some cheese with bread crumbs (Pepperridge Farm) for topping.
Bake in 350 oven for 30 minutes.
Can be made 1 day ahead.
Freezes well.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter; add onion and garlic and cook over medium heat until onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn down to medium-low and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: johnny's aunt gerry's b-b-q sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Heat vineger and add tomato sauce - Remove foam and then add dry ingredients.
Cook slow at least 1 hour.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: kay's apple kuchen(low-fat version)
directions: Cut oleo into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Pat lightly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Arrange apple filling over warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on apples.
Blend yogurt and Egg Beaters and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.

title: chocolate and butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in oven.
Swirl pan to coat bottom and sides with butter. Spread graham crackers crumbs on bottom of pan evenly.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts over crumbs. Pour condensed milk over nuts.
Bake until edges are golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cool, cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and chips.
Bake in ungreased casserole dish at 350° for 45-60 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine melted butter and chips and spread on top.
Bake 10-15 minutes longer.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Put whipping cream and sugar in 4-quart glass bowl and microwave on High for 13 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add vanilla, butter and pecan pieces.
Stir well and drop on wax paper or foil and let set.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Pour over crumbs in baking dish.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together pineapple and cheese.
Mix in separate bowl the crushed saltines, sugar and flour and add melted butter.
Add 3/4 of this mixture to pineapple and cheese mixture.
Place in casserole; sprinkle remainder of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with ham or other meat.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together; set aside.
Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy. Add the eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition.
Add mixture of the molasses and water gradually, mixing well.
Alternately add the dry ingredients in fourths and sour milk in thirds to creamed mixture, mixing until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until gingerbread tests done.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, flour, milk, salt and pineapple juice until thick.
Keep
cool
in refrigerator. Just before serving pour over fruit.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pan and cover at medium-low heat for a couple of hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Brown butter; beat egg real good and add to butter.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 420°; reduce heat to 325° and bake 40 more minutes.

title: lemon-poppy seed bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
In separate bowl mix milk, oil, egg and lemon juice.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Coat loaf pan with vegetable cooking spray and pour mixture in.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix green jello with 1 cup boiling water and 2 cups cold water.
Add crushed pineapple and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let set until firm and while it's setting, soften Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring pineapple juice to a boil.
Remove from heat, add cream cheese and gelatin.
Mix as well as possible.
Let cool.
Beat Dream Whip according to package directions.
Beat this into cooled juice-cream cheese mixture.
Pour over firm jello.
Let set 1 hour or longer. Mix red jello with 1 cup boiling water and 2 cups cold water. Cool, then pour over the other layers and chill until firm.

title: glazed popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl.
Heat butter and syrup in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in sugar and Jell-O; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce to low and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour syrup immediately over popcorn, tossing to coat well.
Spread popcorn on foil-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan, using forks to spread evenly.
Bake for 10 minutes at 300°; cool.
Remove from pan and break into small pieces and serve.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, Kraft French dressing, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, onion and 2 eggs.
Shape into oval loaf.
Place in shallow baking dish; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place on baking sheet or heatproof platter.
Combine potatoes, beaten egg and Miracle Whip; frost loaf with the mashed potatoes.
Broil until lightly browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frosty lime punch
directions: All liquids should be cold.
In punch bowl, combine pineapple, grapefruit and lemon juices and lemonade mix and water.
Carefully pour in carbonated beverage.
Add sherbet.

title: rich church dessert
directions: Blend the flour, walnut meats, brown sugar and butter and press in a 12 x 8-inch baking pan or dish. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: cashew pimento cheese spread(no oil)
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as a dip, on toast or sauce for vegetables.
Can thin to consistency you want with water.

title: chocolate raspberry torte cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 4 round pans.
Cool on wire racks.
Put raspberry filling in between layers.
Frost sides with cream cheese.
Cover and top with remaining filling.
Spread and serve.

title: mock angel food cake
directions: Mix cake flour, sugar and hot water; let set overnight.
Next day, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add rest of ingredients and fold into overnight mixture.
Can be baked in tube pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine and cook covered at 300° for 5 hours.

title: mock drumsticks
directions: Will also need 30 skewers.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: In a 10 to 12-inch skillet over medium heat, place olive oil. Crumble ground beef into skillet and cook until all pink is gone. Add onion, garlic, basil, chili powder, salt, cumin and cayenne pepper. Stir and cook until onion is tender. Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and pinto beans. Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no beans dip
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat just until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve warm, with raw vegetables (celery, carrots, etc.).
Even French bread slices are good. Makes 4 cups.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring dry Jell-O and crushed pineapple with juice to boil. Cool, then add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: tasty casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken polo credo
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour, brown in oil, then place in casserole dish.

title: pilgrim pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat pumpkin with all other ingredients (not whipped cream) until well mixed.
Place pie plate on oven rack and pour pumpkin pie mixture into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Let cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until half done.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise and soup together.
Drain broccoli and onion; add to soup mixture. Pour into large baking dish and sprinkle on cheese, then stuffing.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Chop chocolate fine; add sugar and milk.
Boil to a rolling boil approximately 20 minutes over medium-high heat to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir with pan in cold water until stiff.
Add nuts if desired and stir quickly into 8 x 8-inch pan (coated with Pam).
Put in refrigerator to set hard.

title: special k bars
directions: Heat syrup, peanut butter, sugar, on low heat to a slight boil. Add Special K cereal and press into a buttered 9 x 13 inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and bran.
Mix wet ingredients together and stir into bran mixture.
Mix dry ingredients into wet ingredients.
Put into lined muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: dang good pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour, vanilla, coconut and pineapple.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until center is firm.

title: venison baby tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour soups over meat.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and stir until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll dough out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 6 minutes, then stir in sugar.
Fold in pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread into a well-greased and floured large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: worm cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add noodles and stir until they are completely coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let harden.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine the dry ingredients; gradually add to the sugar mixture.
Fold in the apples, raisins and walnuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 X 5 X 3 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 60 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: italian goulash
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Slice onions into rings and separate.
Puree tomatoes in blender; set aside.
Brown spaghetti in oil straight from the box; drain on paper towels.
Set aside. Brown meat in oil; add tomatoes, tomato paste, onions and seasonings.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Cook browned spaghetti in boiling water until tender; drain off only half of the water.
Add meat sauce mixture and cover.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: no peek stew
directions: Stir all ingredients together in 4-quart casserole.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Don't peek.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook all ingredients (except butter and vanilla) on medium heat, stir constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Blend half of mixture in egg yolks, then stir in mixture and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Pour in baked shell and top with meringue.

title: jiffy cake dessert
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 12-inch dish according to directions.
Cook pudding to directions.
Add cream cheese.
Blend together.
Add drained pineapple.
Mix and pour over cooled cake.
Let set in refrigerator several hours.
Top with Cool Whip afterwards.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Chop celery, onion, garlic, & parsley; add to chicken stock. Cook until the vegetables are tender.
Add noodles and allow them to cook.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cream of mushroom soup and chicken.
Simmer.
(You can saute onions, celery, and garlic in butter if you can't let the soup cook long.)

title: beef chili dip
directions: Mix and melt in saucepan.
Serve in crock-pot or fondue pot with corn chips or Doritos.
Keep warm.

title: sauerkraut meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pat into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for 1 hour or until brown.

title: fudge
directions: In a large pan, bring sugar and milk to a boil slowly and boil for 20 minutes.
Put rest of ingredients in a large bowl and pour hot liquid over; stir well, then beat until thick.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: beef and rice fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large Dutch oven type pan. Saute mangos and dump into beef mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the preceding ingredients, except nuts; shape into ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.
Roll in chopped nuts. Chill until ready to use.
Better if made a day or two before eating. Serve with crackers.

title: prima pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing; toss with 8 ounces pasta.
Mix chopped or sliced vegetables.
Add chicken, if desired.
Cover and chill 1 hour or more.
Toss before serving.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Heat butter and saute onion until translucent.
Add corn and cook until soft.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add half of corn mixture to food processor with eggs, cornstarch and cream.
Add salt and pepper.
Process until smooth.

title: cherry nut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and salt, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well. Spread 2/3 batter in a thin layer in an ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Spread the cherry pie filling on top of batter, spreading to edges.
Drop remaining batter in small bits on top of the filling.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Makes 60 (1 3/4 x 1 1/2-inch) pieces.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 or 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter over butter in the pan.
Do not mix.
Spread fruit over batter.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat ingredients together with mixer.
Place in small baking dish or three small baking bowls.
Generously sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes (until very bubbly).

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Use bacon grease and brown chopped onions and garlic.
After browning, add hamburger and brown at medium heat.
Add salt, pepper and oregano during browning.
After browning, add tomato paste, tomato sauce, green pepper and mushrooms.
Stir all well, then add 6 ounces of water.
Stir again.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix
sugar,
shortening
and
eggs thoroughly.	Stir in milk and
bananas.
Sift
together
and stir in flour, baking powder and
soda
and blend in salt and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake until it tests done.
Serve warm or cold.
Bake in 350° moderate oven for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel and cut rinds into 1 1/2-inch pieces and soak overnight in a mixture of lime and water.
Drain and wash several times.
Place rinds in a large cooking pot and cover with clear water.
Cook until tender and drain.
Boil sugar, vinegar and pickle flavoring together and then cool.
Pour mixture over rinds and let stand overnight.
Then, bring rinds to a boil and boil until transparent and pack into pickling jars.
Pour hot syrup over rinds and seal jars.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave cheese and butter on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix together sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Add to cheese and butter. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and cut.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and blend in applesauce.
Sift together several times the flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Dissolve soda in 1/2 cup boiling water and add to dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together well and pour into a long cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Does not need to be iced.
Will stay moist and fresh as long as there is a piece left.

title: chicken cha-cha
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix soups together and pour over chicken.
Prepare stuffing as package directs and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover the first 45 minutes.
Uncover and brown the last 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Arrange pecans on bottom of pie shell. Carefully pour egg mixture over pecans.
Bake on bottom rack of preheated 400° oven until knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: 2 chickens cooked, boned and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook 10 oz. spaghetti as directed.
Melt 3 Tbsp. margarine and add 3 tbsp flour in sauce pan.
Add 3/8 c milk and reserved chicken broth 1 1/2 cups.
Cook until thick - add salt and pepper to taste. Saute the following:
onion, celery, pepper, garlic.

title: sweet and smoky chicken
directions: Slice onion in casserole dish.
Put chicken on top.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Heat and mix the 2 cups broth with the stuffing mix.
In a large casserole, layer 1/2 stuffing, 1/2 chicken, then pour 1/2 of combined mixture of soups and oleo on it.
Layer again, then pour the rest of the soup mixture over it.
It will be soupy.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put in a large boiler.
After it begins to boil rapidly, boil 30 minutes longer. Then put in sterilized jars and seal.
You can put the soup in freezer if you want. It's very good.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix preceding ingredients in order listed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain.
Toss with olive oil.
Refrigerate.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate again.
Just before serving, whisk together dressing.

title: applesauce gingerbread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Stir well.
Combine applesauce, molasses, oil and egg in a small bowl.
Add to flour mixture, stirring well.
Coat a 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
Spoon butter into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heavily grease and lightly flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or three 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place layers of cooked zucchini, onions, peppers, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, sprinkling of Parmesan cheese and croutons in large casserole dish.
Repeat these layers.
Top with generous Cheddar cheese, croutons and Mozzarella cheese.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: elephant stew
directions: Dice elephant into small pieces; takes about 2 months.
Add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene stove for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people, but if more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but only if necessary, because most people don't like to find hare in their stew.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg, milk, baking powder, flour and salt.
Mix well and put in bottom of 9 x 9 inch pan.

title: german chocolate cool bars
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Press into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Grate or finely chop 1/2 package of the chocolate; set aside.
Heat remaining chocolate and milk in medium saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
With whisk, beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Cool 5 minutes.
Fold in 3 1/2 cups of Cool Whip and the grated chocolate.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Spread remaining whipped topping over chocolate layer. Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and pat dry.
Thickly slice.
Dip into cornmeal, flour or fine bread crumbs seasoned with salt and pepper.
Shake off the excess coating.
Saute tomatoes until lightly browned in a butter-oil combination or in bacon fat.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Thaw shrimp. Mix together all ingredients and pour salad dressing over, allowing to marinate overnight.
Serves 10.

title: merry munchies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Stir in raisins and walnuts. Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in upper third of oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: basque salad
directions: Cut potatoes into large chunks.
Cook and cool.
Cut tomatoes into large chunks.
Slice onions.
Mix mayonnaise, horseradish and vinegar to taste.
Mix into vegetables.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to slow (325°).
Beat butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy.
Add water. Sift together flour and salt.
Add to butter mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in oats until blended.
(Dough will be quite stiff.)
Shape into candy canes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in
preheated 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Frost canes with thin white confectioners sugar frosting.
Stripe with thick red frosting.
Makes 24 canes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix in a gallon container.
Finish filling container with water; refrigerate.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes approximately 30 servings.

title: deviled steak
directions: Pound flour, Accent and salt and pepper to taste into round steak (or deer steak).
Cut into 1 to 2-inch cubes.
Brown in heavy skillet.
Add onion, chopped and sauteed.
Mix catsup, Worcestershire sauce, beef stock or bouillon and chili powder, then pour over meat.
Stir to dissolve crumbs in skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until fork-tender.
Add water during cooking if needed.

title: crispy microwave chicken
directions: Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet over Medium-low heat until melted.
Stir in potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until potatoes are brown, 5 to 8 minutes.
Dip chicken into egg and roll in potato mixture.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, with thickest parts to outside edges in rectangular microwavable dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches).
Cover with waxed paper. Cook on High (100%) 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cook 8 to 12 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough into
1/8-inch
slices.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with slices
overlapping
slightly
but not touching pan's edge. Bake at 350°
for 16 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on crust.
Arrange fruit on top.
Glaze with
marmalade mixed with water.
Chill and serve in wedges.

title: willy wonka's shock it chocolate cookies
directions: Bring cocoa, milk and margarine to a boil (about 1 to 2 minutes).
Put in peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir together and take off heat.
Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: cold bean salad
directions: Drain juice from beans.
Heat vinegar and sugar; add oil and seasonings.
Pour over beans and diced vegetables.
Serve chilled.

title: pineapple cheese dish
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Mix pineapple and cheese together.
Then pour all together and pour into oven glass dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over top, then pour melted margarine over this.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until tops brown and are crusty.

title: virgin island kallaloo
directions: Boil salt meat until tender in three quarts water.
Boil fish; remove bones and add to stock.
Add crabs.
Put greens, okra (from which stems and tips have been removed), onion and garlic through grinder.
Add to stock and boil rapidly for about 30 minutes.
The addition of vinegar prevents the appearance of slime.
Do not skim while boiling.
Serve with fungi.

title: christmas stolen bread
directions: Combine well and drizzle on bread.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine with all other ingredients in a large pot and simmer about 2 hours.
This soup freezes well.

title: quick and easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together slowly in a saucepan over low heat, continuously stirring, until all melted.
Pour into a square buttered dish and refrigerate.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat and stir all remaining ingredients well.
Pour over chops.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Last half hour pour rest of onions over top.
Finish baking.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Make cream sauce with melted butter, blending flour and adding milk.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add yolks of eggs and salmon.
Stir well and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Put in buttered casserole with straight sides.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
